content: I pick a Sleep Story to fall asleep to at low volume on my cell, within 5-10 mins I'm out like a light. Cell turns off when selection ends (each has a time listed on it) App is easy to use, can rewind/fast forward. Large selection to listen to of Sleep, Music, For Children, Meditation, Masterclass. Even has Idris Eldra narrating a story! My HMO Kaiser Permanente pays for its members to have this app (see if your health insurances too!) and if they ever stop I will pay out of my pocket for it.

Amazing! Before this app I couldn't sleep, I suffer with awful anxiety and would worry all night. I took the plunge and paid for a year's subscription about a year ago when my mental health got really bad. I'm so glad I did, it's helped me so so much, my kids also love listening to calm kids on it and it helps my son, who has autism to sleep too. I will definitely be renewing my yearly subscription this year.

Amazing! I can find a session for whatever mood I'm in. When I don't have the energy to meditate I can just listen to a story or just the soundscapes. Multitude of teachers so you can find the voice you enjoy guiding you. The visuals and navigation in the app are pretty intuitive. I recommend this over Headspace, which was a bit too quick for me. Calm is more gentle in its approach. It really helps with grounding.

The best collection of guided & unguided meditations and mindfulness practices/techniques you will ever find in one place BUT, for me, the real Gold, is the Music, especially the SLEEPüò¥ section. There is such a diversity and so much, that if you listened to it all, you'd sleep 4 seasons in one month! Pure Sand from the Sandmanüé∂ü§´‚ú®üò¥

This app is essential if, like me, you have anxiety that gets in the way of enjoying life. Tara Levitt, the main voice of the meditations, has the most incredibly soothing and inspirational voice. The meditations are carefully crafted to teach a valuable lesson, while invoking a calming sensation. There have been moments where I've cried after a session. I love this app, definitely worth a subscription.

What a wonderfully, beautiful app. Just what I needed, thank you :) I have noticed most giving 1 star reviews are because you have to pay after the 1 week free trial. I didn't expect something of this high quality to be free, there's no adverts and it's like purchasing meditation courses, self help, music, sleep help and more all on one amazing app. ¬£28 for a whole year is such a fair price. It's a very proffesional app, I am happy to pay as no free app could come close to this quality.

Wonderful app! I use it every night to help quiet my mind and get some good sleep! I had some subscription issues and reached out to the developers. They responded very quickly and took care of my issue professionally and with ease. Thank you!

Well, what a surprise this is turning out to be, thoroughly impressed! Addendum to this review: Not only do I find the app and it's sleep stories great, in aiding my journey to sleepyland, but the customer service is just AMAZING!! Huge shout-out to Ana, for clearing up an issue I had today. Thank you, Ana!

I love the sleep üò¥üí§ exercises and stories. I just downloaded it tonight but I can really see ow this is the go-to app for everyone. I love it. I will definitely be considering this app to everyone for stressful workdays, general meditation exercises, relaxation and overall deep sleep. I üíï it. To the creators, I would definitely like to see more bedtime stories for kids, maybe some more Disney inspired stories. Not from Disney themselves, but inspired by them.Ty again for a great app.GODBLESS

A week ago I gave terrible rating because I thought they removed the music from being free, BUT they just removed the free offline option and that's ok, please never take the music away. GREAT APP, you have to pay for most of the meditations, but you get great features for free: Beautiful backgrounds, perfect noices, open meditation timer, breathing exercises, the music and the check ins options that are just genius. THANK YOU CALM! I AM SORRY FOR THE BAD PREVIOUS REVIEW, BUT NOW IT IS LONG GONE

This app is my absolute favorite for meditation. There's a lot of content even added daily, and the collections are great. I even like the background soundscape. I have chronic insomnia and this app had been the only reason I feel asleep many nights. the sleep meditations are great. It's worth the money for me.

$70 annual subscription to access a variety of content that constantly expands - comes out to $0.20/day to invest in your mental health and well-being. I love the daily meditations, sounds, and stories. Everything has been thought out in advance and made available in the app so I don't need to spend time googling suggestions which takes precious time. One of the best investments for my self care and that's priceless.

my beautiful, but very "energized" 6 yr old granddaughter loved it! She paid attention (amazing!) & interacted verbally to all the questions until she drifted off to a deep beautiful sleep. üíï I also thoroughly enjoyed it. I loved the approach. I think we're both hooked. üôÇ Thank you. * namaste

This is a truly awesome app. I've been meditating for about 3 years now and using the app for 2. There is massive benefit to meditation, if you have an intense job or chronic pain or bereavement or anything of this nature. Tamara the lead meditation guru who speaks most of the daily meditations has a soothing and well planned structure; often with a daily message which helps one reflect and gain perspective in our busy lives. I would strongly recommend.

The absolute BEST meditation app I have found!!! I can honestly say I use this app at least 3 times a day! It has amazing meditations to choose from, sleep stories that work, awesome motivational music, ways to document your progress and soo much more! I never thought I would pay for a meditation app but here I am! Definitely worth it! This app has changed my life ‚ù§

I can't believe how relaxing this app is. it's got a really wonderful interface and pictures too. Just a joy to use. The train sleep stories are my favourite, hardly ever fails to send me to lullaby mountain.

Mind blowing! My 4yo falls asleep from proper crazy to narcolepsy in minutes. I always read her a bedtime story but she's always too interested in pictures and talking about what is going on in the story to fall asleep to it. Now she's "dead" 5 minutes into the story. I have also tried the app to soothe myself even though I never believed in such things but have to admit app content makes wonders, really. Highly recommend to all sceptics. Worth every penny of 28¬£ a year fee.

Really great in creating self-awareness, and acceptance. Its great for motivation. Learning to experience and acknowledge our emotions. Combined, with breathing exercises, yoga, body scans, a plethora of mind, body, and spirit, techniques to help us cope with day to day life.

Love this app. The meditations and messages are relatable and relevant, plus there's plenty of various meditations to chose from. I now find myself wanting to meditate, as opposed to forcing myself to, because the Daily Calm and Daily Trip have such good little tidbits of wisdom in them.

Love this app! Have been using it for I think 8 years or so now. Some months consistently when the need for structure was higher. Some months not so much. Whenever I do get back to it, it's exactly what I need. My favorite is the 10 minute loving kindness meditation. It honestly changed a difficult relationship and I shifted from feeling underapreciated and resentful to respected and very much valued‚ù§Ô∏è it was incredible to me to experience everything I could do myself and with love and ease‚ù§Ô∏è

Sitting and breathing, centering myself with meditation ... it truly does make me feel peaceful, clear and focused. I'm inspired already after just one meditation experience. I definitely need to make time every day for meditation. A whole body experience. üßò‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

Love the daily meditation, so short, simple and very effective. The different choices of 'noise' from white noise to rain drops.... are extremely relaxing. Lots of stories and meditation choices. This has become my 'go to app' ‚ù§ It clearly states its a 7 day trial with an annual charge of ¬£28. Those complaining, didn't read or don't value their mental health. I think it's an amazing app which is helping lots of people during the pandemic üåüü§©‚≠êüå†üí´

Used this app for the first time last night. WOW!!! I felt very stressed out when I laid down to sleep, around 9:30 as I had just been watching some of yesterday's üì∞ news. First, I started out by listening to the Nile story. Must have fallen asleep very fast because I haven't a clue how it ended. Changed to the " crackling üî• fire" sound after my first "bathroom run", then to Ocean üåä waves. Just woke up at my usual time, a little after 5 AM. Unlike most mornings, I actually feel REFRESHED!!!

I have been meditating since 2019,mid year. This was amongst the first app I had and I subscribed for a year in 2020. I have done many types of meditation since then. I bought the full version to become more consistent esp in terms of mindfulness which can be applied anytime, anywhere in any circumstances even without this app to help oneself deal with the current circumstances in life. Great job! Keep updating and adding new contents!

I was doubtful but keen for meditation to work. It now helps me from my most traumatic nightmares and brings me back. Each day I start my day with Either the daily meditation or with the anxiety meditation first then later the daily meditation. It is more easily helping me cope with my severe trauma ptsd. try it, there is nothing to lose and everything to gain.

Wonderful app. I would really like the option to cast to my google home mini or to the chromecast. My phone speakers aren't very good, and it's a hastle to bring out and connect a blue tooth speaker instead of connecting to something already set up.
So many guided sessions, exercises and even resources for children. It covers a variety of topics and life events. I would highly recommend.
I subscribed last year and the app has helped me sleep better! my only ask would be is if we can queue up Sleep Stories like in a playlist because sometimes I get jolted awake when the story stops.
Calm is amazing! I've never meditated before in my life but since I've found this app, I meditate everyday! It's so peaceful and relaxing. I love the way I feel after each session! üòÄ

absolutely love this app. I have been trying for years to learn how and practice meditation unsuccessfully, until now! Thank you Cam for truly living up to your name! Well worth the the price of especially now! this is an absolute direct way to battle this pandemic! I would give it 10 Stars if I could

I like the options you have and how you can add comments about how your feeling on the day through your comments and choices it picks what you may need to help you relax. I recommend trying the 7 day free trial.

I use this app with my students to teach them how to self-regulate emotions, and I use it for myself to help me fall into a deep peaceful sleep. I've also shared it with my friends who suffer from anxiety to help them with their breathing exercises. Honestly, there's so much that this app can do. I absolutely love it.
very useful tool, straight forward and easy to use- its simple intuitive design makes it easy to slot into or create a daily routine would highly recommend

I wasn't into meditation until now I found a couple of apps and tried it. it is without doubt the most effect way to relax. I haven't explored much, but the range of subjects seems large, I am excited to find out moreüëç
Its been over a year and I'm clearly aware of the changes in myself. A queue option would go a long way on this app. Bringing seamless transitions from one lesson to the next.
Its the best meditation app available. Has everything that you need to get better at your meditation practice. Cuts the clutter and keeps you calm.

This app has helped big time during the first covid lock down, don't think I would have survived without using Calm every day & night. I still listen to the daily calm now that the 2nd lock down has been easier.

I love how easy is to start a day with the friendly remainders,, just by setting the time is most convenience for you, I love to begin my day with just 15 min of meditation and gratitude... Thank You Calm, I'm very grateful!!!
Love this app! I've never learned how to meditate before. This app guides you and really works to calm.
I have always done daily meditation, but the past several months I had found it getting harder and harder. Calm has helped me in numerous ways to get back into meditation, easily.
I love this app so much but the only thing I have to say is that I don't know where the favourites for sleep is. Can you ‚ô• sleep? But other than that, this app is amazing!!!
what an amazing app! it's like having someone right there with you speaking to you in a calming reassuring voice. This has helped.me immensely!
The app didn't work on my phone initially despite having paid for the full year subscription. Customer service have been a great help in getting this resolved.

it's a great app whenever you feel restless and absorbed by chaos just open Calm and listen to one of the meditation routines,your whole day will go well and I am not saying just for the sake of saying it's that good

I paid for a years worth and Love it... I'm Sure Every One deserves a little Calm with this pandemic going on... This app is very expensive but so worth every penny... If You Have the money to splurge on something, I recommend splurging on this app...

This app was made for ME! I can select a CALM item to add to my CLOCK app for gentle wakeups. I can drift off to sleep listening to an amazing voice telling me a soothing story. I can choose a Calm listing anytime Im feeling anxious or sad, which in these trying times is often. Much better than TV or sorting thru audio apps. Try it. I yhink youll love it as much as I do.
I didn't realize how much I love this app until I was without it for a month. I tried other apps, but none of them resonated with me like Calm does.
I love all the features, music, programs to calm and center the mind that Calm provides. I am still exploring and finding new and helpful avenues.
best meditation app - no "pressure" to show up every day, amazing narrators, plus music and other options. the kids meditations are appreciated during COVID as well!
I love this app. It helps me when I was very anxious. calm can calm you from inside.üòä
i used the 7 days of sleep part one and I knocked out. I've never been able to close my eyes and instantly fall asleep after listening to something.
This is the app I reach for each morning to start my day anew, while I'm studying (the nature sounds tune out all the external noise), and to wind down so that I have a peace-filled sleep.
A soothing app, although you have to pay AUD 79.99 for a year after a 7 days trial, but it can be worth it.

learning how to meditate is very important. I really appreciate how he gave me something to think about, therefore I use this education to better my life and lower my stress. I will start a routine for myself and take time out each day to do exactly what he says. Thank you Lebron for the Inspirational word. Take Careüôè‚ù§
Only had this app a month and it has helped me so much! I have only touched a tiny amount of its content so far but use it every day.
I love this app.I used to sleep with occasional nightmares,now I'm sleeping (CALM!) I am very truthful and very critical with app reviews!
I really love the timed breathing feature on this app. I use it at least twice a day for 5- minute check-ins with myself.
it's a wonderful app. the guided meditations are as per my initial check-in and they were very helpful. thank you Calm team

I've been using this app for years. The background sounds help me focus by blocking audible distractions. The sleep stories help my son get right to sleep. I really like Jeff Warren's "How to Meditate" series. I agree with people who say that a wider range of voices would be good. Also, most meditations are ten minutes, follow a similar structure, and have you focus on the breath. More variety in lengths, structures, and objects of attention would be welcome.
Very calming, and it has many different options for those trying to get into meditation (like myself)

I did this while amid an anxiety attack. Though I advocate for self-care, meditation, and therapy, I've never been very good at practicing it myself. This app has unequivocally helped me personally with my anxiety in a way I've never experienced, and I would wholeheartedly recommend it to anyone who is struggling. Please do yourself a favor and download this app. It may just save your life.
I would 10 out of 10 recommend!! Free version is great, but paid subscription is 100 worth it

This app is wonderful! I needed something to help with the anger, anxiety, and frustration I've been filled with due to social media, the news, politics. This app makes it so easy to learn and practice mindfulness, which helps quell those storms. I'm starting to be able to actually practice those more trying commands of Jesus to love my neighbor as myself and to love my enemies.

This app has become an essential. I have a difficult relationship with sleep and this helps me refocus my mind both at night and in the mornings. Excellent app. It would be cool if I can get it to load the recordings I want via Google Voice so I didn't have to look at the screen within an hour of sleep. Maybe if each recording had a code and you can ask Google or Alexa to play that specific audio. May also be helpful to those who are visually impaired. Please let me know if this can work. ‚ò∫Ô∏è

I love this app it has changed my life. I really enjoy the sleep stories. The softness in the voices is so relaxing. I also enjoy the reminder to go to sleep at ny chosen time. There are so many things I love. **I would really like if they added an alarm to wake up to.. some calming sounds to wake up to would be awesome. ** Thanks calm!

WE LOVE THIS APP! We are half way through our 2nd year and it has been worth every penny! We use it for sleep, meditation, and for brainstorming. If you need background noise, they have it, guided meditation, you betcha, or let one of the many different narrators read you a bedtime story! There are stories for all ages, my favorite being the trail stories or trains. Can't say enough good things. Now they are offering a lifetime membership for $159 through 01/31/2021. The only reason I wrote this review today is because I was looking for where to pay for this offer. If you are considering it, just do it. Only $59.99 a year. So worth it!

this is definitely a positive investment into my well being. I fall asleep so fast it's unbelievable. I work both days and night shifts alternately, so my sleep schedule is way off. Knowing all I have to do is put this app on and I am automatically transcended to a place of dreams, it sounds unreal, but it is. Thanks for this.
Possibly a bit too good, I fall asleep within 2 minutes of listening to the sleep stories so never get to hear them.

It's true that you need to pay for the good content but if you search hard enough you can find discount codes. I really love this app. It's helped me loads. I first found it when I was struggling with insomnia through a period of anxiety and haven't looked back. There are dedinite improvements to be made like being able to save a series and going back on suggestions made as part of a check in but I find it so valuable
Love using this app as a great way to wind down at the end of a busy day and for getting my boys to fall üò¥ üòä.
Its the best relaxing app you'd ever find . Just needs a bit of payment . But its totally worth it
great app. easy to use and love some of the background sounds during meditation sessions.

Well worth it! Offers so much more than just meditation. I have been enjoying my free trial and fully intend to keep it going into the paid subscription as long as the fantastic content keeps coming. I love the meditation classes, daily sparks, curated playlists and soundscapes. Calm body is also a fantastic pre and post workout cooldown session. You have nothing to lose by trying it for free! But to me its more than worth its cost. What better investment is there than ourselves?

I can't rate Calm highly enough. It's helped me get to sleep even when I'm at my most anxious and panicky. Well worth the subscription fee. For those thinking of using the free version, it's still good but the content is very limited. It's a while ago now but it was just one sleep story that changed every month I think. You could see the other content but weren't able to listen to it. But honestly I'm super happy with it so far, and glad I ended up subscribing.

I came to this app a couple years ago for help sleeping but discovered so much more. Admittedly, yes this app feels a little expensive but after canceling my subscription for a few months I realized how valuable this app was to me. I love that if I'm ever feeling angry or anxious or even like I just need to clear my head I can open this app and I know there's something here for me. Tremendously helpful üëç
Helps me fall asleep, and the short guided meditations are great for taking refreshing breaks on busy days.

Meditation is something I never really dedicated myself to 2 years ago. This app not only helped me practice more consistently but aided me in meaningful ways with anxiety, stress and depression during what was incredibly low time for me. I purchased the full version, you need to invest in your mental just as much if not more than your phydical. We even use the sleep stories to help my little one fall asleep within 10 minutes every night. This has helped me take control.
I really love this app, helped me already a lot for meditating but also for to fall asleep. üñ§

I can't really thank this app enough. My subscription just renewed so I realized its been over a year since I first started using calm. I was in therapy and we did guided meditation in session, but I needed so so so so so much more of that headspace to find peace. I've grown a practice that has changed a lot over the year, I've been flexible, and forgiving of myself for obstacles I've navigated, but I always come back to my breath and I thank Calm for that (and Tamara Levitt)!!

This app has changed my life! I think more positively, I sleep amazingly. The music that you can select from is so eclectic and especially unique. There's so much to catch your eye and your ear. This would be an excellent gift for your loved ones struggling with depression or insomnia. Thank you Calm!

The library of meditations is pretty wide, so it's easy to find something useful. The structured guides work really well too, and can help focus and work on existing issues. The daily calms help to keep it interesting. Headspace wins on its "learn to meditate", but I prefer calm for continuing this journey. The part I love most about calm is the sleep stories. I listen to one every night and it helps set me up for sleep.

I love this app, the premium is well worth it for all the content available. I've learned alot of valuable knowledge and also managed to get a handle on my anxiety and depression, next step is my sleep and I'm so far enjoying the sleep stories and bed time stretches! Will 100% be striving to invest in the one time purchase as I have integrated this app into my daily life and it works so well.

Didn't think this app would work but it far EXCEEDED my expectations I love it. I can sleep it helps with my anxiety helps with my breathing absolutely in love with this app would recommend it to everyone I know. My husband has tried meditation in the past but couldn't get his mind to stop he can do this one it helps him fall asleep we put it on a Bluetooth speaker and he is out very quickly.

my daughter has a hard time going to bed at night. the kids stories are excellent. i also like that some of them start with directions to relax, soften your tense areas, and settle in for sleep. one night, the story we listened to defused an outright screaming tantrum. whoever thought of this app, THANK YOU SO MUCH!!!

Great way to calm down. I paid for the subscription, and use the soundscape feature every night. I also use the music playlists to help me focus at work (so my music app stops suggesting classical and starts suggesting music for my off hours). One feature I would like: the ability to cast the music to my smart speaker (Google Home) so I can have a nice speaker during my work day.
The sounds are great and and multiple different podcasts and meditation packs make it so you never run out of content üòÅüòÅüòÅ

I was offered a free annual membership to Calm through my Kaiser health plan. I'm sure by now anyone who watches TV will have seen the frequent Calm commercials. I had no plans to get this app, but now that I have used it a few times, I gotta say it's a really good app. Having prayed but never medidated, using this app has been a new and pleasant experience for me. Give it a try.
awesome tool for trainingüëçüòé helped me to train to be present, calm and relaxed.

I have always suffered from anxiety. these past 2 weeks have been the hardest I've ever experienced. 3 days ago I had the worst day of my life. this app has helped tremendously. last night was the first night I slept with no anxiousness
Love Blue Gold sleep story by Stephen Fry sleep immediately! App is very fluid and comprehensive with managing sleep, anxiety and general well being‚ô•Ô∏è

I've always been a light sleeper and decided to try this out as my credit card offered one year subscription. Well, day one, I told my wife that I woke up in the same position I went to bed and slept hard and didn't move. Day two slept very well. Today, and day three, I overslept work first time in 15 years. It is a mystery to me how it happened, but I guess the app works. If I get fired from my current job, I will seek restitution from Calm in a form of direct employment.
Great app, I use it to help me go to sleep everyday. The whitenoise works wonders!

I love this. I am really impressed with Calm, so impressed until instead of doing the 7 day trial, I paid for the year subscription. Thank y'all for this because this is something that's really needed in this over barring stressful world. This is not only amazing, thank whomever created this and blessed the world with it. Thank y'all for creating and making a huge difference for many. My life has been so very truly affected in such a major and positive way. Omg, my apologies but I could go on...
The single most useful and beneficial fool I use towards cultivating a more positive mental platform. I am hooked!

This is the best app I've ever had. I don't normally write reviews but I wanted to say thank you to the makers as it plays a central role in my life now. I do 2-3 meditations a day and after years of having to stay with my children till they fall asleep, they're now happy to be left with an excellent sleep story. Life changing.
Am still a novice in meditation. This app looks great, it's actually very good I my opinion.

So good, definitely recommend upgrading to the membership, it is so worth the money, I use it every night without fail and it has helped me so much with my sleeping. It used to take me hours to fall asleep but after using this app for just a few weeks I started to fall asleep in just 20-30 minutes. I got this app 2 years ago now and I still use it everyday. Highly recommend!
Great app! sends me off to sleep every night without fail... very quickly

Went for the 7 day free trial. Loads of options, not just one as some people say and I wanted to try meditation for a long time but didn't have a clue what it really was or where to start and this has helped me know what the basics are. Like the ocean sound to fall asleep to as I always fall asleep on the beach. So I think I'm going to pay for the year and let my husband try it as he wakes during the night

Love this App so much and been using all the free stuff for quite a while now, I didn't need to and wasn't prompted to but I decided to purchase a one off lifetime premium membership, I'm so glad I did. I suffer with Anxiety/Depression/Panic Attacks/Insomnia, and I'm also a born worrier with the added worries of my poor health re: Heart/Lungs/Low Immune System, and of course Covid-19 fears. So this App is the main thing keeping me sane. Much variety of help to be had by using this App üòÅüëç
It has helped me with multiple areas of my life. It's not selfish to focus on yourself some. If you're in a good place with yourself the world around also benefits. This app helps me do that.

Downloading this app was one of the best decisions I have ever made. I live more in the moment and I feel my life is richer for it. There are so many different types of meditations to try depending on my mood or circumstances. I use the sleep stories for myself and the kids, the masterclasses are fabulous -I think the LeBron James Train your mind series helped me focus and excell in an exam while working crazy shifts. As my practice grows this app grows with me. Well done Calm team.

Great selection of activities to support a mindful practise to life. Not just meditation but many ways to focus your mind on the present and support you to bring more balance to your daily life. I'm English and initially found the American accents in much of the meditations a little challenging but the content is important and being less reactive to the accents is actually a chance to develop that skill anyway!

Love, love, love this app. So much variety to choose from. The daily calm is perfect for a quick re-focus. If I could rate it higher I would. Edit Jan 2021 - stil love it! Use the 10 minute calm every morning for a great start to the day. Thanks Tamara and team.
First time that I tried it and it put me to sleep before the story ended. Great for people who have a hard time falling asleep.

It feels unique and pretty , the guide "how to meditate is really good" even I've meditated for some time before. Lots of stuff is locked and u must buy it but it's okey, u can use this app even without buying anything. I recommend it to u ‚ú®üßöüèªüçÑ‚òÄÔ∏è enjoy it with love !

Great app, good variety of narrators, however many of them have similar voices which makes the selection a little bland imo. 5 stars nonetheless....... It would, however, be especially awesome if they were able to recruit some narrators with more distinct voices. It would be exceptionally comforting to hear a bedtime story narrated by Gilbert Godfried, or perhaps a flashback to the 90s with Pauley Shore as a narrator???
This is the best app that I have ever used and when I can't sleep I turn on a sleep story and I immediately fall asleep.

ER nurse approved. I use it daily to help me unwind. I'm also super ADHD and in a stressful job so the quick sessions offered are above and beyond. I can stay focused (well, relatively so) and feel less restless after a quick session. It takes practice and isn't a cure-all by any means, but well worth the subscription.
I received the app from a friend. I use it everyday and it is helped immensely. It's helped with my anxiety. I'm calmer and more focused.

started with nightime stories and half hour of the most relaxing sounds such as the breeze through the leaves or the fireplace crackling. quickly moved on to 7 nights meditation and then 7 days in the morning after a little 10min morning yoga stretches, its helped my head, anxiety, anger levels, stress so much along with other things I look into such as samadhi, its helped change my life for the better...so far so good

The CALM offers guided meditation and individual selections. The option to rate emotions, before and after, is very helpful. You can record your daily moods, gratitude and reflection. These comments are available in history, great information when working on a particular topic or with a therapist. The app, is easy to navigate and access all aspects. The cost is acceptable as it replaced other apps into 1 place. I recommend this app. I actually look forward to doing my daily meditation now.

I really like the app and it helps me fall asleep better than any medicine could! I love the Daily Calm from Tamara ! I also had a problem starting the app today but I just reinstalled it an now it works again perfectly! Thank you calm for helping me reduce my anxiety and give me new perspectives on the worl around me and the little universe inside of me ‚ù§

Great mindfulness app. There are some basic meditations for free but to get the full benefit you'll need to pay for the subscription. some great meditation series for different things such as managing stress or relaxing the body or dealing with loss or pain. I also like the daily calm - 10 min meditations each day that introduce new techniques or reinforce existing ones that I do before work every day. I've been calmer, more resilient & more open to new ideas since using this app.

I love this app so much. it has helped me when I have deep depressive episodes and when I'm anxious. the music is beautiful and calming. I love the stories and they have such a wonderful masterclasses section with amazing people who share great info on different topics. highly recommend!

The essential app for people with anxiety or fear of sleeping. l once had PTSD induced nightmares/night terrors and grew afraid to go to sleep at night even after they went away. It was so bad I used to lay in bed for an hour and a half before finally passing out. This app has become a lifesaver. The 1/2 hour stories are so calming and soothing that for the past several nights I've found myself falling asleep before I even get to the end. If you struggle with sleep anxiety, you need Calm.

Great for the whole family. We all use the app, to different degrees. My husband and I often do meditation together. My neuropsychologist recommended the breathing exercise as a way to help my faulty autonomic system. Our kids love the sleep stories for bed. We have them listen to them on long car rides to help them get some sleep, too. We are happy to pay the premium cost for an app like this.

This is an elegant and simple-to-use application which provides voice guided meditations, soothing music for various meditations, and the voice coaching is very good. In addition, you tell the app what you want to focus on and it will give you meditations that are related to those topics. Also, if you need to, you can download any of these to your phone for offline use.

Calm is totally living up to its name. I didn't think I needed another meditation app and clearly I was wrong. I love the soothing voice, the meditation methods used and the background music too. I also appreciate that the background music can be adjusted. I have fallen asleep many times to both meditation and the sleep stories. This is a great app for anyone wanting to meditate or who has insomnia. I highly recommend it!

I was lucky enough to receive a one year subscription through my doctor's office. I find the daily meditations very helpful and easy to follow. There are also a variety of nighttime stories that are interesting and have different themes, narrators, etc. I plan to look into the Masterclasses more as I think that will further my meditation. I will probably renew my subscription when my gift period comes to an end.

Only 1 gripe with this app is the UI. I use this app to fall asleep quite often, and the super bright blue and white background that pops up is rediculous. White and blue lights send signals to tour brain that wake you up. Please think about changing your start up screen to a darker color so it's not blinding those of us using your app in a dark room when we are starting to get tired?!

I love this app. I was just going to do the free trial, but I'm considering purchasing it. It has helped me get better sleep and I've felt so much better throughout my day. I usually use the evening wind-down stretch, followed by listening to the Matthew McConaughey story, then the wake-up stretch in the morning. I also love that there aren't any ads.

I couldn't be happier to have found this app. I have been using Calm for over a year and a half now and it has added so much to my life. You learn so much about yourself and ways of looking at life better. You learn to relax and let stress melt away with the Daily Calm meditation. If you need help with sleep they have sleep stories that I have yet to hear a story all the way through as I fall asleep before it is over. I love the scenes during the work day where you can listen to water, wind, crickets, rain falling and so many more. There is a Calm Master class every month where you learn so many different topics that you can apply to your everyday life. There is a new Calm body with short yoga sessions for different parts if the day. I do this during the afternoon, at work, when I need a little break and it refreshes me to continue with my day. You won't be disappointed with this app. I highly recommend it to anyone and everyone! It has changed my life.

I absolutely LOVE this app :) I suffer with neuropathy and insomnia, it has been a true blessing helping me to relax and sleep. I have used it EVERY DAY since I ordered it. (almost a year now) Unfortunately I won't be able to renew as I am on a fixed Soc Sec income and it's just not in the budget. I wish it was less expensive :(

With my experience, Calm is the best I've found that gives me relaxation in the most elevating ways. I get a great nights sleep and when I wake up, I listen to a more stimulating experience for the day. It's awesome!! I might just add to this I feel better mentally and emotionally not to mention I am less anxious in stressful situations. Calm is an experience that keeps me coming back for more.‚ò∫Ô∏è

Just started using this app. Free version is wonderful. I set a beach scene to go through the night to a low volume and it helps me relax as I breathe with the slow rhythm of the waves. Having a hard time sleeping and this app really helps. I also have a diffuser by my bed with lavender essential oil as an added element for relaxing. Decided to unlock the full version and for all the meditations and try out the stories. Feel that the price is worth it ($5/mo).

This app has helped me a lot. Most specifically when I wasn't able to seek help from a therapist. I bought the year long access and was able to choose from the different categories what I wanted to work through and adjust through a wide variety of topics as difficult emotions evolved. The tracking function is wonderful because though I'm not able to commit time to this practice everyday, my overall body of work is still recorded and celebrated, which helps to continue motivation. Gr8ful 4 dis :)

I used to pay for hypnosis therapy; this is the same if not better quality meditation on all levels. The detail and options are fantastic. My sincerest thanks to the developers who made this so easy to access, share, and use positively! I am honestly amazed at the amount of thought put into every app feature: the app is always giving options with NO PRESSURE. I will be a lifelong user, keep up the beautiful work.
Just listened to the music is calming
What a great app that helps with focus and relaxation! :)

I've been using Calm for a couple years now and love everything about it. When I slip out of my meditation routine, I listen to Tamara's meditations to get me back in sync. I love the Music they've created and will use that as my background sounds for meditating on my own. There is a wide array of meditations to choose from depending on what's happening in my life. I can't sing enough praises for Calm! It's the reason I have stuck with meditating for this long - and I truly appreciate it.

I suffer with anxiety. It increased over the past year with death of my husband. Needless to say stress and anxiety has come in ways never before, but with this app....I'm always relaxed I can sleep without waking up in the night. Anytime I need to relax this app is wonders!!! We need meditation at times but using what god has given us naturally to relieve some of life's anxieties is always the best way to go! This app is great for that.

Love this meditation app. So many different guided meditation tracks such as 7 days of self esteem which guides you through recognizing self destruction through our thoughts or thinking we must accomplish something in order to have self worth..these revelations have been so calming to my mind. I'm really excited to continue to explore all the options Calm has. Been sharing this with a lot of my friends who also can be hard on themselves and they're loving it. Thank you so much. God Bless.

It's a great app. They've got guided meditation, relaxing and focus music, wonderful sleep stories and great visuals/scenes to relax. This app has singlehandedly helped me be stay healthy (sane) during some of the most stressful times. If you can afford it, it is worth every penny. I understand the reason behind the costs - they update their content continuously and the content is very helpful. I do wish they had a monthly subscription option though.

I started using this app about a year ago at the recommendation of my therapist. It has really helped get me through some tough times. I've used all of the different tools you can use (Sleep, Meditate, Music, Breathe, etc) but my favorite tool in this app is the "Sleep Stories". I bought Bluetooth headphones to listen while I'm going to sleep. I can't tell you how many stories I know the beginning of and have never gotten to the end because they always get me sleeping! Thanks Calm team!

This app is actively saving my life, assisting with my balancing and re-centering for which I am eternally grateful with reminders and short videos I can use between clients. It's easy to use and I love the many hidden gems. My young clients really love their section as well. This app is amazing and I cannot say enough about it. Thank you all!! Definitely everything you need in a meditative space exists right here without the brick and mortar. üëçüëçüôè
quick reminders and mantras to make your day a little better

Calm is an excellent app! very well done. simple to use yet elegant in design. im really enjoying how i can customize the background and music or white noise. the quality of the meditations and music are above my expectations. and the Breathe feature is si helpful for creating a mindful breathing practice. i haven't tried the paid version but the masterclass trailers seem legit. good job, way to go!

I really enjoy what this app gives me in lieu of an actual therapist right now. I appreciate that topics are categorized in ways that I can match the emotions I'm looking to process and even though it took me a really long time to finally start exploring it after paying, the lessons in patience and understanding have made me come to terms with the wait that it took. I like that it tracks my meditations and I'm able to see the overall bulk of work I've done even if it isn't a daily practice. üòäüëç

Thoughtful app with many wonderful and effective features. I've been using it every day for the last month and I'm so thankful that I took the leap! The daily calms and meditations are new to me, someone who works all day everyday, but I am glad to take 10 minutes to myself every morning. The app has resources and strategies for many forms of anxiety, (including sleep, plane and travel, etc) these are great and much less expensive than medication or therapy!

Excellent for teachers and students. I use this app daily for my personal practice. I have also shared with my students. We use it in my school for staff self-care, too. A nice upgrade would be for the background music or waves to continue after the Daily Calm finishes. I often continue to meditate after Tamara finishes the guided meditation and it changes my focus when the background stops.

I LOVE this app. It's worth every penny... $70 (or whatever it is) is very little cost, considering I listen to it 365 days out of the year. The only criticism I have is that stories (or meditations or calm body, etc.) cannot be deleted individually... ALL of them have to be deleted. It's a pain when I just want one gone... I have to delete the entire category and then download all my favs over again. I wish you would change that!

I truly enjoy reading the negative comments. If you have half a brain, you can figure this app out! It is simple, straight forward and easy to use. I love the option of it going to the sleep sounds after the sleep stories are through. I use the nap features almost every day and the sleep stories EVERY night! The only suggestion I would make is to have multiple readers for the same story. I'm not a fan of Mr. Sklars voice. I do not find his voice soothing at all but I like the stories he reads.

This is a great app for meditation and sleep. I'm so happy the calm schools initiative is helping me teach my preschoolers. Daily use for 2 months has made a significant change for the better in the way I engage with my fellow humans. A very big thanks to everyone who keeps the app up and running. I recommend this app to everyone and anyone who is ready to become the best version of themselves.

This is one of the most wonderful apps I own. It's moderately priced with others like apps and the voice of Tamara L, the guider, is very calming and beautiful -- in the end I chose this app because I like her voice. In fact, everything about this app is soothing by design -- the layout, the colors. They keep adding more features -- sleep stories and specific guided meditations. The only thing that would enhance this experience would be a connection to a community of people who use it.

I try to use it everyday, it makes a huge difference in my mental health. Recommended to me by a counselor. I was in a dark place, diagnosed w/ a painful condition (cervical stenosis w/ 2 herniated discs & thoracic outlet syndrome). I was grieving the loss of myself, my youth, my body, & my ability to take care of myself & my 3 year old daughter. Meditation taught me how to cope w/pain, rid me of panic attacks, taught me to love myself no matter my circumstances, & so much more. Thank you! ‚ô•Ô∏è

The Calm app is, in a word, transformational. It is teaching me how to strip away the noise that is a constant in our busy 21st century world, and guiding me to center. It is giving me tools to use and teaching me the importance of being present. After only a few days using this app, I am sleeping better and able to focus more fully on the moment at hand versus a thousand moments. It is giving me peace, particularly during the stress that surrounds our world currently. Even in chaos, I am calm.

The substance is great. I enjoy this every day. It helps me become aware and discover new concepts. Please try to define concepts, even like meaning of letting go or release. Don't assume we understand every simple term the way you do. Please note: this app is hard at times to t on, get off. Still a difficult app to use. Has a mind of its own. Fades in and out, goes on and off. But the end result is worth it. I enjoy Ms. Tamara's daily sessions immensely.

Very well-composed app. Excellent for meditation. I love the sleep stories. It would be nice to have some longer ones ( at least an hour ). Also I like the selections of music. The stats help keep me motivated to continue, and I have found it very helpful to relieve stress. The one year subscription for premium is worth it. Update 11/25/19: Still enjoying this app very much. Works smoothly, no freezing. I only wish it would turn itself off at the end of the bedtime story to preserve battery.
Please don't send me notifications to breathe through out my day. other than that amazing how fast it makes me fall asleep, I dont ever remember making it thought a 30 min sleep sound.

I love Calm! I was skeptical at first and thought it might not be worth the cost. I couldn't have been more w:rong! I've struggled -with insomnia and depression for years. Since using Calm, I haven't made it to the end of one Sleep Story. Sweet, blissful, night-long sleep finds me before the story ends. Then to wake-up and do a Daily Calm has made my days much better. Thank you Design Team! You have changed my life!!!

I have severe anxiety and depression. this app has saved me countless times. I even use it to help my nephew calm down when he get ants in his pants. Lol! The breathing techniques are amazing. When I try to count my own breath I get really bad anxiety, but with the option of them saying it for me, I can soley focus on my actual breathing. I absolutly love that the app creator keeps adding new things. So many people are different, and the wide range of calming tools are very appriciated.

Simple and several options. whether it's breathing techniques, meditation, or help getting you to sleep this is a helpful app. you can set a reminder as well if you want to do it at a specific time each day. has been very helpful self guided meditation. still on my 7 day free trial, not sure I want to spend the money for a subscription but it has been helpful and relaxing so far.

A very necessary tool in my insomnia kit! I had no idea how many different ways that I'd be using this app when I chose it: to supplement my meditation; to read me a story narrated by actors (!), helping me to fall asleep; to provide soothing, custom-tuned white noise; to provide a beautiful picture as a focal point to start my meditation. I'm sure that I've forgotten a few! It is a well-curated app that has daily updates with new meditations and stories. It is worth the subscription fee!

This app has changed my life, and i do not say that lightly. I used to suffer from panic attacks at night, unable to fall asleep. Now I use their guided meditation to help me drift off to sleep. It has become a part of my daughter's bedtime routine as well. After we read books, a sleep story helps her to sleep as well. It has made practicing meditation accessible with their wonderful "daily calm" series. I love the recent addition of morning, afternoon, and evening stretches!

I love my Calm app, it keeps me on track with my meditation and gives me a variety of different ways to keep mindfulness in mind throughout my day. I wish that they would add more master classes I loved their one on screen addition and one of the more recent ones about how we are basically all living in a world that is moving more towards wanting robot speed instead of organic speeds and how we should all sit back and relax a bit. That one was great to listen to on the train before work.

I love everything this app has to offer and I use all of it: the soundscapes and music, the meditations, the breathing and movement exercises, the daily check-in, and most of all the sleep stories. To say Calm has changed my life is not an understatement. I used to have horrible insomnia at times, and could not turn off my mind. The sleep stories have completely changed my sleeping experience, giving me something calming and lovely to focus on and fall into a deep, restful sleep to.

I've been dealing with a lot of anxiety lately and my doctor suggested this app. After taking time everyday to do the daily meditation I have noticed a difference in my anxiety. I've been able to stay calmer about things just by applying what I have been learning. My favorite part...the nightly sleep stories. sleep has never been better! try it and see for yourself!

It always helps me sleep. Love it! edit: I uninstalled it because it expects me to be rich enough to pay for premium. I always used the same sound because it was the only one that worked for me. and now i have to pay for it. Before this happened though it was an amazing app. Definitely recommend. Just wish there were more options for non premium sounds.

I've struggled with/lived with panic and anxiety for 40 years. This app is really helpful and has gotten me back on track using techniques that have helped me over the years. After listening to sleep mediations I am walking each morning refreshed for the first time in my life. No internal tremors. I suggest listening to master classes even if you think they don't relate to your exact challenge. You'll still get something out of them.

LOVE Calm. It's my primary meditation app alongside Insight Timer. However, I HATE the main narrator's voice, Tamara. I change it to John whenever possible. Unfortunately, his voice is not always an option. Tamara use to talk normally in older series; but now she does this weird sing-song, high to low pitch, warm-smiling, uneven toned reciting that is distracting, unenjoyable, and very annoying. I still find Calm much more useful than Headspace due to its techniques and applicable habit changes.

This app has really helped me de-stress before bed, so that I can sleep better. It also provides calming nature sounds and music, when I need to tune out background noise, at work, to focus better; and fit in a quick meditation or breathing exercise, when I'm having a stressful day. There's a different meditation, daily, in addition to the library, so it never gets repetitive (though you can save and go back to your favorites). Overall, it's the best meditation app that I've found.

I have this app on my Iphone. I was saddened when my subscription ended and had to go back to the free version, which I'll admit is pretty lacking. Then COVID -19 hit and money is super tight and I, even loving the app, could not justify 70.00 for it for one year. I was able to find it for 40% off and did repurchase premium. YOu guys do a good job, and the app has helped me a great deal in staying mindful, the meditations, the check ins especially important now with the state and breadth of this virus. Maybe you could find it in your company's heart to beef up the free version for the next several months? In the long run Calm could virtually end up with thousands more paying subscribers. People remember acts of kindness and it comes back around doubly to those who share. Love this App- am hoping you will reach out to the millions of hurting people right now and beef up the free version! Thank you!

Amazing app! I did not believe at all that it would work, seeing that I wake up in the middle of the night quite often, and once I'm awake, I can most definitely never fall back asleep. Ten or twenty minutes into "The Story of Abuntu", I was fast asleep. The sound affects in the story helped a lot. God Bless and thank you to whoever made this amazing app!

I love this app! Iv only been using it for a couple of days because i got a free trial, but it has really helped me alot. I really love the power of meditation and honestly can't place any mundane value that is meaningful enough to not just say this straight.... I FUCCS WIT THIS APP HEAVY ON ME!!!!!

I've always come across this app before, and I've always been skeptical about it. So I decided to do the trial and the first night I was hooked. I fell asleep immediately. I forgot to cancel the trial period, during which I didn't use the app once. It was a happy accident, as I use this app almost daily. I love the Calm app. It has so many good and useful things in it, it's really a great value. Excellent app for a variety of situations. I personally use it nightly to make it easier to fall off to sleep and during the day to rest when possible. Amazing!! Just a suggestion I don't have the money to spend on this sort of thing but I will use it as often as I can as it does improve my sleep.

The simple fact that I received an email before the end of my trial reminding me that I will be charged if I don't cancel, along with instructions about how to cancel, makes this the absolutely most costumer friendly app I have ever used. The bedtime stories have helped me fall sleep faster than ever, and the stories usually focus on sensory experiences that whisk me right to dream land. The cost is high, though, and I'm going to see how my sleep is impacted without the app before buying.

I love this app! The premium content (I got the annual sub) is necessary to get the most out of it though. But then you have so many choices/way to help you meditate, sleep, or just relax. using only the free sessions at the moment, but the content seems really helpful and relevant to modern life. Update: after around 25 free sessions, I bought the yearly subscription. It helps fall asleep and I love all the things on there my favorite is the sleeping ones

I started using "Calm" nearly two years ago during a bout of extreme anxiety. I was a little skeptical about spending the $70. To be honest its not really a smart financial decision on my part for various reasons. However, this app has been incredible for me. I suffer from high anxiety, and insomnia and this app is so wonderful. sometimes my partner and I will turn on the soothing sounds and use them as background for romantic, comfortable dinners. There is so much to love about the Calm App.. I first tried it to help me develop a bed/sleep routine. And it worked for me, from the reminder to get ready for bed to the sleep stories. Being a Mom of now a 15 month old, my sleep pattern is all messed up and I wasn't getting any rest. My body was use to getting up several times a night. I found this app and I love it! it help me sleep and relax I love THIS APP

I initially had the 7 day free trial. I literally listened to a different sleep story every night. I have PTSD/Anxiety/ INSOMNIA. I have tried salt lamps, melatonin, sleeping meds. I like the narrator. going to get the yearly subscription and try to stick with it. If I end up developing super powers, I'll be sure to update this review. The guidance in this app in fantastic. Everything is well-spoken and beautifully presented. This app is simple but effective. I've never meditated before and this is perfect for me. I have found it sets a calm tone for my day. UPDATE - this app is advertised as Free but it seems to be only a free trial and then you must purchase for approx $70.00 per year. Im so disappointed. 10/18/19 UPDATE...Im hooked. I love that there is a daily calm for a quick pick meditation, I seem to find it is usually very fitting to what's going on in my life at that moment almost like it is tailor made for me personally.
