This app let's me know that I'm not alone in my struggle and that the struggle isnt a necessary part of life., Only the contrast allows us to see more clearly what we are wanting!

Love this app I use it for myself and my son it's very calming helps my son sleep love the stories for kids and the mediation and the relaxing music. Cannot complain about anything. Download the app it will not disappoint I have the limited version. You can get a trial for seven days or pay a yearly fee of $59.99 which I think isn't a bad idea really overall awesome app.

I like the way I can keep a log of all my meditations. I especially like the "breathe" function. Of late, I see a problem with the log. It says below "n minutes - just now" but in the calendar it marks yesterday and not today. This problem has been happening for the past couple of months.

Amazing app, got the lifetime subscription 2 years ago and its totally worth it, I try to use it everyday, and the developers are always adding more to the app. They have voice guided meditation practices for stress, sleep, happiness, and there's even a voiceless freestyle meditation that lets you go as long as you want. There is a huge variety of relaxing background noises that you can choose from. I will never stop using this app.

Love this app. Used the free version for awhile and ultimately decided to get the premium, which is totally worth it IMO. I usually take some CBD and do "The Daily Calm", a new 10min meditation, every day, when I crawl in bed at night. This has changed my life. Not even joking. Sometimes I'll do the "7 days of Anxiety" or if I'm on a plane, the "Calming Flight Anxiety." Great sleep stories, one even narrated by Matthew McConaughey, who has a very calming voice. 100% recommended this app!

Love this app! It's been a really amazing tool. I used to use Pacifica, but I feel like this is so much more useful for meditation. I got a six month trial from Samsung and will definitely be renewing it. Thank you! My favorite parts of the app are the sound scapes, scenes and breathing bubble. The only thing I would improve is more options on the breathing bubble.
Very good meditation music

I love this app! The Daily Calm session itself is helpful but there are so many other features that I use as well... the music during my workday, the sleep stories at night. I also like that I can favorite meditations that are particularly helpful so I can go back to them again if I'm struggling with the same issue on a different day. I would highly recommend this app to help control stress and anxiety, and to build better daily self-care habits.

I love this app! The daily guided meditations are often spot-on; I love how there is new content to listen to every single day. The various soundscapes and music help me to get into a zone. The programs and other options such as PMR/body scan, sleep stories... all really great stuff. Add in the lovely animated wallpapers which in and of themselves are relaxing... I just feel more calm as soon as I open this app. So much content that is well worth the $60/year! Thank you for helping me, Calm.

The 'sleep stories' and 'sleep meditations' are life savers for someone with sleep issues like me. I absolutely love this app. However, I would love to some new sleep meditations and new sleep stories added more frequently. Also, the app typically shows stories as 'new' for weeks even after I've listened to them. But, hands down - one of the best sleep tools I've found since 2007. Oh, and - I saw someone's review about the app being glitchy; it never happens to my paid app.

Eva Green sold me on this one. I thought Calm was all white noise and meditation exercises. But they have bedtime stories for grown-ups read by actors. I had no idea that was a thing, but now I am hooked. Completely worth it. The stories are basically tableaus - positive and hopeful without being uncomfortably new age. Bedtime stories for grown-ups. Who knew?
it helps me sleep a lot

After using the free trial of this app for months, I bought the full subscription and have subsequently used this app nearly everyday for over a year. It has meditations and sleep stories for whenever I need. No matter my current state or emotion, I am able to find something on this app that helps. The sleep stories are also very helpful and lovely to use at bedtime. There are always new features being added, and I'm not sure how I used to live without this app.

I am very young and love this app. It has wonderful exercises and they can vary from 4 minutes to hours. This is perfect for before school and if you need to fill your day. The exercises get me ready and positively thinking about my day after. I also love that you can set reminders for every day so you dont get off track.

This app is much better than Headspace. I find the voices more soothing and the meditations more like a combination of yoga and therapy. In only two weeks, I already feel like I am recognizing thought-patterns, able to pause and examine my emotions. The soundscapes (rain, waves ect) as background are excellent additions too. I'm excited to try all the different aspects. I was hesitating on the price at first because I hate "subscription apps", but the price is exactly right for what you get.

I have never enjoyed meditation, or found it useful, but recent stressful events in my life made me realize that I currently don't cope with stress at all. This app is helping teach me how to calm down, breathe deeply, and give my mind some time to relax from the stress. I always feel renewed when I finish some meditation now, and the daily reminder alarm helps me keep my mental health a priority.

This app has improved my mental health, my relationships, my healing journey, my parenting, and generally, my outlook and quality of life. I have learned that there are many thoughts that I have habitually hung on and repeated in my brain which are negative or just useless. Using the lessons and practices in this app, I am figuring out how to recognize and release these thoughts so that I can use my mental bandwidth more positively, effectively, and efficiently. The premium content's worth the $

At 1st I thought it was a bit pricey because I only wanted sleep sounds. But after the 1 week trial and I saw the meditation exercises, stories, and body stretches I was hooked. I love the download option so I can use it when I travel to places with bad internet connection. I recommend getting the 1 week trial and using something different every day to see if it's worth it to you!

I've been a subscriber for years, because Calm does so many things just right. I use the daily guided meditations and masterclasses regularly, and I like several of the other features (sleep stories and mood tracking, for example). My favorite thing about the app is the team's commitment to improvement and innovation; they're consistently making their great service even better. Highly recommend!

I love it!! I use this app to help me sleep at nights, and it work. In the last 3 months I've been having trouble going to sleep. On those nights when I go to sleep I wake up in the middle of the night and can't go back to sleep. Several days ago when I saw Calm advertised on TV I decided to check it out. People, it works!! Let me encourage you to try Calm, I believe you will like it.

This app may seem expensive. but it is worth every penny. It is indeed calming as well as uplifting. Meditation, calm music, sounds and soothing sleep stories by talented authors, composers and readers contribute to it's high quality. I requested as others did too a variety of meditation leaders as is provided for stories, as initially, there was only one AND Calm has provided them! Wow, they pay attention to their customers. Now I would really like a simple way to close the App.

I love this app. I bought the subscription and it was worth it. I use the sleep meditation a lot and I love they have a new meditation everyday. They are short and sweet so you can start your day off right or end your day in piece. The voice artists are great. Definitely worth the forty or fifty bucks a year.

Update: sometimes I am my own worst enemy, but after straightening out some confusion on my end, this really is a great app! I tried some other meditation apps but none really matched the quality of Calm IMO. I've been using it to relax my high strung self and the options are great for whatever I feel I need at the moment. Try it, I think you will agree.

I LOVE this app! It's such an easy and convemient way to cultivate mindfulness, gratitude, relaxation, and better sleep. I use the sleep stories and nature sounds all the time for myself and my kids and they really work. The ability to schedule notifications to remind me to meditate in the morning and before bed is so helpful. I'm also enjoying the stretching and exercise videos and my kids like to join in. I'm looking forward to trying the master classes soon. Tons of high quality content.
I see ads for this app all of the time so I decided to check it out it's really great and helps me relax so I can fall asleep

I love this even more since the upgrade. Usually i dont like upgrades and end up deleting app. But this one is even more amazing Not really liking the latest update. It is very annoying to gave a pop up of what i did when i clearly know what I did. And it is slow so when i want to go to another group of meditation i have to wait for the stupid pop up

i downloaded this app, and to be quite honest, i didn't have very high hopes for it. well i signed up and all that good stuff, and my mind was absolutely blown! just within the first 10 minutes if that, i have already fallen in love with the way that it is set up! i love the meditation tracks; the voice of the woman in them is so oddly relaxing! and just overall BLOWN AWAY by this app!

This is seriously one of the best apps i have ever experienced. There is even a section for children and teens, and as a parent, i really appreciate how thoughtful and thorough this app is. Great stories read by great narrators and are always updating the story library. This whole app for the win. Totally worth the money. I tend to rarely spend money on apps, even when i enjoy them, and would rather just do without whatever features cost money, but the Calm app deserves to take my money!!

Honestly I was skeptical before using this app! I was juggling two careers, one being a new one and both self employed, plus family etc. My brain at times felt like an out of control pinball machine. I often times felt I was drinking out of a fire hose.....I knew I needed to quiet things down in my head and soul or I wouldn't last very long the way I was going. Calm changed that for me! Literally within the first few sessions I noticed a difference in my efficiency while working. I also noticed how much more relaxed I was in day to day living. I have recommended this app to a multitude of people, family, friends and clients I wouldn't be without it!

On my own, I've always struggled to get my thoughts to stop to allow me to meditate. The coaching on this app helps with that. I consistently succeed. This slow down is refreshing and helps me manage my daily stresses. Each session is 10 to 15 minutes. I do 3 or 4 per day. When a session is over, with my mind clear and me calm, I am able to have more meaningful prayer as well. I also appreciate the teaching on equanimity. The awareness of the concept alone has helped me begin work on it.

I've done 7 days of a 30-day meditation program. I love the instruction, it's explained so simply, it makes it easy to understand and remember. The instructor's voice is nice too. I find I'm already using various aspects of meditaion throughout my day, automatically, when I need to relax. I like the bedtime stories too. I'm very happy with "Calm". There is even a section that plays the soft sound of crickets and song birds.

I love this app. I downloaded it years ago, before the subscription. I would get on frequently to go through timed/guided meditations. I stopped using it for a while. I came back to see a lot of new content. There's a lot of good stuff here for people who need it, and I would highly recommend you take the time to go through it. If it feels overwhelming, pick one section to start with, and go through some of it. There's something here for everyone.

Calm has been a fantastic app so far. I've had it for three days and used it every night so far. I have extreme problems falling asleep, it usually takes me two or three hours of tossing and turning... I've fallen asleep within minutes using Calm. I enjoy both the stories as well as the nature sounds. One thing I personally would love to have is more/bigger thunderstorms, or a good thunderstorm backing track for the stories. All in all though, I definitely enjoy and benefit from Calm.

Absolutely love this app for my toddlers 3 2 and 1. They look forward to bed time because I can position them all for snuggles and be hands free or hold my phone where they can see the scene on the story. They are all asleep in less than 30 mins. I love this bc instead of nonsensical fairy tails you have educational material playing and they are learning. Money well spent.

This is a fantastic app! I am learning meditation by doing the Daily Calm, and the sleep stories are great, I use them every night and they work like a charm. I have also gained benefit from some of the Masterclasses, and I'm sure I'll use even more of the app's features as time goes on. But for me just the sleep stories alone are worth the cost of the app!

I LOVE this app! Specifically the Sleep Stories. I've always had a hard time getting to sleep and staying asleep, but I have been using this app for less than a week and I am already noticing a difference in my sleep cycles. I also enjoy the variety of meditations available on the app. I would recommend this app to anyone who is looking to get better sleep at night or who wants to get into meditation.

Before Calm, I had never meditated or even given it a chance, but one particularly stressful day, an ad just caught my attention. I started with the trial and was hooked immediately. The app was wonderful at transitioning me into the life changing practice and has made me feel more in control of my anxiety, body and general emotions. I cannot recommend it enough, especially for those hesitant to go to a studio in fear of those "newbie" jitters.

This is the most focus I have experienced in this my starter journey into meditation. Also, I thought the sleep stories was a silly concept, but I'm falling asleep before the story is over. I woke up a couple of times during the night, as I do a few times per week, listened to another story, and back to sleep I went. I didn't expect this much peace and sleep.

Really rich content. The meditations I have tried are short yet very effective. I can improve my day enormously in just five minutes any time of day anywhere. There's a lot of informative content to which I didn't expect and I enjoy. I also really like the options for children, I've tried it with my daughter and she likes it! Great set of tools and options. Thanks!

I was hesitant to purchase the app and pay for the annual fee, but after having it for a few months I would absolutely recommend Calm. It has meditation, stories for kids and adults, and sleep music. The meditation and sleep assistance is what keeps me coming back on a daily basis. I have never meditated before this app, but now love doing it. They are short 10-15 minutes, and have great healing properties.

I tried this App as a guest pass and loved it. Subscribed. Theres new content added regularly and you can pick favorites. I love it so much I became a lifetime subscriber. Worth every penny. I did not meditate before I had this app, now I can't imagine not meditating! I like the morning stretches too. Just try it- you'll love it! Be sure if you don't want to pay for the app that you cancel before your 30 days. You'd definitely know after the first few times using it. It's a keeper!
This has really improved my mental health overall, thnx so much!

"Calm" is very soothing, I had been having trouble sleeping as of late, but not so much now with the app. I love the sleep stories and the music both are very relaxing. ** I have been using Calm for almost a year now! It is super helpful, I use it when I get stressed at work, when I'm studying, and to help me sleep. The soundscapes are great for white noise- really helps me focus when I study because it 'scrubs' out background sounds.

Amazing 10 min. Different Meditation everyday with educational, therapeutic information and a simple quote at the end of each session. Her voice is so soothing and perfect for this, I could listen to her all day. Its perfect for me because my time is short so I do it in the morning before I leave for work. They also have longer sessions and other longer meditation for sleep. I had the 30 day trial and then got a year subscription. I told my buddy about it and he now listens.

I absolutely love this app. The calmness I feel after the daily sessions really helps to change my mood and give me energy to move forward in my day. You can get the most out of it if you are consistently using the app. The topics can relate to people of all backgrounds. Beautifully done! Definitely worth the money.

I love this app!!! So much of it is free, and everytime I use it I almost instantaly fall asleep. An amazing feature is that you can download the music so anywhere or time you can listen. Also it has everything! From rain to sleepy time stories. I haven't yet tried the meditation part but I am sure it will be amazing as well! I use it almost every night. I found this app because I couldn't fall asleep. I tried multiple apps however this is the only one that worked perfectaly!

This app has been an incredible tool for my personal self care. As a classroom teacher, I spend 10+ hours on my feet dedicated to the care of others. If I can unplug from the world and plug-in my headphones to spend 15 minutes with Tamara just once or twice per week, the benefits are tenfold. Looking forward to increasing my dedication to this practice (and mySELF) in 2020!

Far more features then I realized, there are little nooks and crannies in this app that i keep finding. When I first got the app, i was very hesitant to sign up for the subscription, glad I did. Make sure to poke around in the other areas, very well done content with daily mindfulness meditation, videos, music, and longer meditations.

This app is EVERYTHING it says! I sometimes have trouble falling asleep & tried a sleep story & when I woke up, it was HOURS later, I couldn't recall the story finishing or anything after & it happens every time I use it! Very relaxing meditations, I'm still new 2 it & can't wait 2 try other features. This is a GEM, truly. THANK U!

Meditations are just the right length to easily fit into a busy day. A quick perspective adjustment through meditation is always good for focus and health. The sleep stories are wonderful at bedtime - better than any sleeping pill. I have yet to make it all the way through one because, well, I fall asleep! Wonderful app!

Instead of listening to audio books to get to sleep you listen to adult bedtime stories meant for you to fall asleep to. It totally works even better! I listen to the music more often than I expected. I'm able to use the same premium subscription on my work phone and my personal cell phone (Android and Apple) which is great for traveling or if my other cell is running out of battery. I have not regretted my premium purchase at all- and will buy again in a heartbeat.

I just need a little help getting to sleep sometimes. I can turn the light off and the app reads me to sleep. I think I've only heard the end of a story once! There are also some white noise options which can be great. My favorite is wind blowing thru snowy pinesüíö. Might seem like this app is a bit of a luxury item, but we all know now how important sleep is to overall health. I just got in on the black friday lifetime membership rateüíöWow...perfect timingüíö
this is the best app ever if you are experiencing pain or ensomnia or just can't seem to relax. I have been using this app for a couple of months and it has helped tremendously.

I use the sleep stories every night! I have tried other things to help me fall asleep but nothing worked on a consistent basis like the Calm sleep stories. Honestly, I don't know how the majority of them end because I fall asleep before hand. The ones that I do know the ending, it's only because I fast forward to the end! üòÅ And I gladly pay the yearly subscription cost because it works for me....it's cheaper than some meds I've tried! THANK YOU SO MUCH!!! ü§óüò¥

I absolutely love the Calm app! It's a must have for everyone. Perfect for when I have too much going on inside my head and I lie awake for hours which usually keeps me from getting a good night's sleep. It's like a timeout to center yourself and a soothing, comforting way for you to drift off to sweet sleep in Dreamland. I recommend it to everyone! Thank you Calm App, I'm so happy that I have you.

Wow! I never really gave meditation a fair try before, but I've noticed a tremendous positive difference in my whole outlook each day! Even after just a few sessions, I've found myself to be far less stressed, far more focused, and I've experienced a happiness I haven't felt in a long time! I'm genuinely pleased with this app and the people who've made it possible! Two thumbs way up as far as I'm concerned!

A lot of people have complained about this app bc of the price, but as someone who struggles with major clinical anxiety and panic disorder it is worth every penny for me. The meditation sessions work on so many extremely helpful techniques that have transformed the way I handle anxiety. Another feature that has been extremely helpful is the body scanning. It has even helped me in the midst of full panic attacks. I know it's not for everyone, but I hope more people will give it a try.

It's SO AMAZING! Every time my kids can't get to sleep, time for a sleep story! It includes sleep storys for kids or adults. Medatation for kids and adults is also available, as well as breathing training and scenes that you pick out. Though most of them you have to have Premium ($60 yearly), some of the sleep stories and meditations are still available. Even so, Calm has a special deal where you can get Premium for free if your a teacher, in a Homeschool or Public school.

Peaceful rest. I've meditated a long time and have given up the organized meditation that I originally learned. This gentle coaching captures all the essential parts of meditation - the breath, the repetitive nature of cal ing thoughts - without the mantra. The mantra had always bothered me, so after many years meditating with a mantra, I just stopped, but missed the quiet in my mind. So I looked around and found Calm. I am well pleased. Tamara`s voice is so sweet and calm!

I cannot begin to explain what an incredibly positive & powerful impact this app has had on my life. I started out hoping it would help me w/ my acute chronic insomnia but it has gone on to do so much more. Subscribing to the paid features has enabled me to learn about meditation & mindfulness. Two things I really knew nothing about but have become such an important part of my daily life. The Masterclasses are a feature I just started utilizing & WOW, I LOVE THEM . Get this app, it's worth it!

Amazing. What would I do without this ap now? It helps me sleep almost every night and helps me to relax my muscles and unwind. It helps me during tense moments at work when I need a 60 second cool down. It gives me a way to find inner peace. I wish they would add more sleep stories that are based on history, like Queen Victoria by Alan Sklar.

I have severe anxiety and I was very apprehensive that it would work but my therapist suggested the 7 day free trial. I couldn't believe the transformation in just that short period of time. After my 7 days I purchased the premium and do my daily meditation. She gives you the understanding of anxiety and how powerful our thoughts really are. Please give this app a go and please be patient. You will get better at meditating. It's just exercising your brain. Enjoy!

I am in love with this app. Tamara delivers the best daily messages that always seem to resonate. Additionally, I have struggled with sleep and restless thoughts but with the sleep and meditations I have been sleeping much better and felt a lot less stressed in my day to day. The sleep stories are great too! I love some of the celebrities voices. Nick Offerman is one of my favorites, only sometimes I get distracted thinking of an episode of Parks and Rec but totally worth it!!!! Lol!

Not sure why the low reviews. But this is a really good all around app. It's not entirely focused on meditation, but it is good for it. It's also focused on sleep with sleep stories and music, which is what I use it for. I think the meditation lessons are a bit more difficult for beginners than Headspace, so that's where Headspace gets the +1. But I love that for the same price, you get these other sleep sounds and music

I love Calm! I look forward to listening to it every day. It has a wonderful variety of calming offerings. Some of my favorites are the chapters from books (some familiar, others not) designed to provide assistance with falling asleep while listening. No matter how hard--or how many times--I try to listen until the end of each book excerpt, I have yet to attain that goal: I am always already in a deep, relaxing sleep!

update:free content returned and I am satisfied. I do enjoy having the subscription but it's still too expensive so I'll make do. all free content gone! three used to be so much now everything is locked with the exception of 2 sleep stories. so disappointing. and it's too expensive considering you can get this all free on YouTube. this app is constantly running in the background draining your battery. I loved the free content, is was so good that I periodically bought 1 month at a time. SAD!
replyContent: Hi there, I apologize for the trouble accessing Calm Music! A mistake was made when these programs were locked for you. These programs should now be unlocked moving forward. Reach out to support@calm.com if you're still having trouble accessing content.

content: LOVE this app. The sleep stories help me fall asleep so much! I am a new mom and have to get up a lot thru the night to take care of baby and even though I was so exhausted I just couldn't turn my mind off to fall asleep. The sleep stories let my mind focus on the tales and drift to sleep. My favorite narrators are Erik Braa and Stephen Fly - i really wish there were more stories from both of them. After your free trial you can choose how to subscribe - monthly, yearly, lifetime.

Wow this app is amazing, even though I am on my 2nd session on meditation, I feel like a new person. This app is the best app if u are distracted or of your stressed. I recommend this to other people who have emotional problems, they Are distracted, emotional, or stressed. It really helps!! This app is the best‚ò∫‚ò∫‚ò∫‚ò∫‚ò∫‚ò∫

This is honestly one of the best apps you can get for daily mental health and well being in my opinion. Yes, they let you try everything for 24 hrs or something and then everything is locked unless you pay the subscription price. That being said it is well worth the money, I mean how much do we all waste on things everyday that are terrible for us. To sum it up they offer a free week of trial so give it a shot and if its not for you just cancel before the renewal, simple and risk free.

Awesome, I love the many options this app offers for meditating all the way from someone who has never done any meditating all the way to someone who has been doing it for many years. I also love that this app has meditation geared specifically towards kids. The sleep stories are also great. Highly recommend this app!!
I love this app,it has helped me a lotüíÉ

I love this app and can't wait to do it everyday, I developed anxiety, panic attacks and depression after losing my father and the constant stress of looking after my disabled son, this app has been amazing there is so much to do an learn there's something new daily it has been a huge part of helping my problems subside and returning me to the happy person I was, I feel blessed to have found this app, Tamara levitt's voice is beautiful and hypnotic.

My family loves this app. My husband and I use sleep stories every night before bed. There is a wide variety of stories with the subscription, but even the free stories are great. i also work night shift, so I find the stories very helpful to wind down in the morning before bed. My preschooler even asks for a story some nights to go to bed. I also really love the meditations. It's helpful to have the guidance to take a break from the craziness of the day.

It has everything, from meditation to workout stretches, music, and bed time stories - which are great, and there are more added so it doesn't get samey, and a variety of narrators, so that if someone's voice grates on you, you don't have to listen to them. I started with a free trial about 7 months ago and now have a lifetime subscription.

This app is a lifesaver. It's given me some tools to calm myself down when I feel I'm getting worked up, and like a lot of us, I make the mistake of staying up late on my phone or gaming. So often when I decide to go to sleep, My eyes are wide open and I can't sleep. But the bedtime stories have helped that immensely. When I can't sleep, I play my favorite bedtime story and I have never heard the end of it. I fall asleep to it everytime. Thank you calm!

I use this app everyday! I LOVE the daily calm... it's just such a nice reminder to take it easy and be mindful towards yourself. I really appreciate the entirety of the app, w the music, the different lesson topics, and the kids section. Theres more besides just those. I think they're doing a great job and this app has a lot to offer.

I've only done one meditation so far and oddly, for me, I almost fell asleep! That's never happened, it was so relaxing, there was space & when the voice came in they said things that resonated with me. I also like the ability to personalise this app. I'm on the brink of signing up for the premium, just want to see how I go after a couple of days. Because ordinarily I meditate alone without guidance anymore, so we'll see!
I. LOVE THIS SO. MUCH...IT REALLY HELPS. ME SLEEP. WHEN AM. HAD. A. HARD. DAY.. .. . AND. I. FIND. THE. DIFFERENT SOUNDS. AND. MUSIC REALLY. RELAXING....‚òÜ‚ô°‚òÜ‚ô°‚òÜ

Since I don't know how to contact you...I've lost the wonderful sound of my rainfall wallpaper. Why did it go away. According to Ssamsung and Voerizon it is a software problem. Would you fix it please. I really miss that summer rain sound and often meditate just to that sound. I absolutely love Calm and try not to miss a. morning. However, I wish you would respond to my question about the background sound of the app. I still MISS THE RAIIN.

I think the $70 annual fee is a bargain. Quality: The app is intuitive and bug-free; the meditation leaders and story tellers are top-notch; audio production value is high. Value: Tons of content! Yes, meditations but also relaxing nature sounds, music, and stories. Ahhhh!: After 4 months I am consistently (and surprisingly) delighted every time I open the app. Thanks Calm, Jeff, and Tamara for a great experience.

I love this app! I have been really struggling with anxiety for months and am currently taking medication but still struggle every day. I just started this app 2 days ago but it has already helped a lot! I didnt think anything could at this point.... I went to sleep for the first time without TV last night listening to the nighttime story. And the master classes are amazing! <3

The sleep stories are magic... I can flip flop for hours trying to find sleep. When I turn on "Calm" I select a "sleep story" and wow... I never hear the end of the story as I'm quickly and peacefully fast to sleep. This "Calm" app is quite literally, a life saving tool for those who have difficulty falling asleep. And yes, I enjoy the meditation series and all the nature sounds from which to choose. Thank you!

Bedtime Lifesaver for myself and my children! The amount of time it takes for my 3-and -4 year old to fall asleep has decreased by at least 70% since we started listening to the sleep stories every night! This app is the ONLY app that I would genuinely say has made a positive impact on my life. I recommend it to everyone...there is something on there for every type of person out there. Get it!!!!

100% worth going premium. I've had calm for 10 weeks and I've not been able to stay awake long enough to listen to a full guided sleep meditation, without calm my mind is racing and I could be awake for hours on end even when using relaxing breathing techniques. I've recently started to use the childrens stories for my 6 year old at sleep time and they work really well. I've used and enjoyed some of the other features too but there is so much to explore, I wont be getting bored any time soon.

I usually don't do reviews for apps apps, but I have to make an exception for this one. This is the perfect app if you are looking to get into meditation. * I got a free month trial (cancelled my card info after signing up for it so I could try with no worry of a charge, but bought a subscription before the trial even ended because it was so good). * Im on the last few days of the "How to Meditate" course, and I highly recommend doing this one first!

Best investment in my health and sleep, absolutely worth the subscription price. I am incredibly picky about voices for guided meditations and sleep stories, so it's amazing to find an app with so much talent I can enjoy. I particularly enjoy Tamara Levitt and her sleep meditations. Fairly frequent updates to sleep stories and meditations so there's always something new...even though I mostly listen to the same 3 meditations on repeat! Thanks so much Calm team!
Lovely voices and music

Great app. Tamara has changed my life. The only things I hate is the limits on the unpaid version. But content wise in paid version, its the best calming and instructive app I've ever found. Tamara's voice is often the only thing to get me to sleep and helps with ptsd and anxiety. Overall I highly recommend this app and have told all my friends about it. The sleep stories really work too. I love it.
Fabulous way to start the day! Teaching myself to experience "what is", not what I "expect" or "project" my feelings should be.

I started with the free version, but was happy to keep it on for the paid prescription, which I've been using for a couple years now. I use this most nights to help me fall asleep. Love the sleep stories the best. Allows me to focus on one thing and eventually fall asleep, rather than having a racing mind that keeps me up worrying about all sorts of things!

Calm is incredible! I'm new to the app so haven't explored all of the uses yet. I listen to the Daily Calm nearly every night to fall into a restful sound sleep. I use it when I'm traveling. The voices are so relaxing and the variety of voices and nature sounds allows me to select the one for my current mood...calm beach, light rain, mountain wind....

Nothing has ever helped me to sleep. I've had to use medication that I don't want to be on for YEARS. I've tried to find something else that will help. The first time I tried it I fell asleep naturally! I didn't sleep perfectly but I haven't naturally fallen asleep w/o meds for as long as I can remember. I definitely suggest trying this app!!

I absolutely love calm. However, 69.99 payment is a lot for a one time payment. Supposedly there is a monthly payment option? Please tell me where to find it. Clicking premium on both the app and your website only leads you to the 69.99 payment. There's no option for monthly. You could make more money by charging people monthly, just $9 a month is well over your 69.99! I'd pay 9 or 10. Please place a monthly option!

I love the many options and functions in this app. You can pick a soundscape, which is essentially background app sound that you choose as calming. There are guided meditations for different purposes like sleep, anxiety, deep thought, etc., sleep stories, and more. I like for a lot of things with voice, there is sometimes a version with a woman's voice or a man's voice, so you can pick which reader you like more. Personally I like the woman's voice. It is worth it to pay for the app.

Calm is the only app I am willing to pay for. For a while I used only the free version and while I don't recall what prompted me to purchase the yearly subscription, I am so glad I did. I have always struggled with sleep for as long as I can remember and the sleep stories are great for me. I rely on the guided meditation sessions, so while I have tried other apps, Tamera Levitt's voice plays a big role in why this is my favorite.

Tried a few other well known meditation apps and this is the best. If I need a bedtime story, it has that. If I need to listen to music, it has that. If I need to specifically work on an emotion or work concern, it has that. If I want a generic meditation to calm, or even visual scenes with sounds to watch, soundscapes... new content added daily. I have logged many hours on this App and I am no where close to going through all the content. Well worth the investment.

I love this app. I've had the annual membership for a few years now, and I think it's something everyone should invest in. In addition to the wonderful meditation and mindfullness features, there is an incredibly vast library of sleeping tools. I have severe PTSD and sleeping is very difficult for me. This app has helped me to deal with the physical and mental stress of my condition. Most importantly, it actually helps me fall asleep! Thank you Calm team, I appreciate you very much.
fabulous for all ages

One of the best meditation apps out there. Such a great service and tremendous amount of variety for everyone's needs. Thank you so much calm team for this app! Helped me get out of my mind and this bothersome stress from our daily lives. ‚ô•Ô∏èüôè P.s if you guys could bring down the price anyway that would be an amazing move from you because online programs relatively speaking aren't really that expensive and there is so much free content out there.

Learning to relax takes time, but doing a little bit each day really helps. I also love the sleep stories, especially Anna Acton reading "Gratitude" it is soothing and puts me in a positive and happy frame of mind before I fall asleep. Plus, when it gets busy in work and I feel I need to step back and refocus, theres a meditation for that too. 5 minutes and I'm back in the game.

Great app - this helps motivate me to practice mindfulness/meditation daily. I love the ambient sound, and the narration is great. Mindfulness in general has changed my life for the better in so many ways. Whether through this app or some other source, you owe it to yourself to give it an honest try.

Quick response time on support questions. Excellent choices of music and guided meditation for Any moods one might be going thru. Whether you need to destress in the middle of the day, or hear a soft sounding voice that will guide you to sleep at night. Calm Radio has it all, and everything in between.

Calm has given me my sense of self back. It is amazing how I've been able to reconnect with who I am thru the meditating sections. I'd just forgotten to do this over the years. Calm is so much more and offers so many options to reconnect. it makes it easy to take a moment each morning to recenter myself to go thru my day more focused. I will be using this app for a long time.

I have only been using this app for a few weeks, but the meditations are short enough that I am able to maintain focus. Also, the bedtime stories put me out effectively, and the music is relaxing when I need a break from the chaos of daily life. This app really does inspire me to be more intentional in my daily spiritual practice. Highly recommend it!!

I have trouble sleeping and the Calm App really helps me, the stories are interesting and puts you to sleep. As they say how you may know a particular story they have a slightly different version which is great so you try to stay up to hear it, it also allows me to figure out how I truly feel on a daily basis. However I think more descriptive words can be added to the list, there are times what I feel is not listed but you can write how you feel...Keep up the good work guys

So far I have used the app nightly for a week. I have mild TBI and PTSD that I've suffered from an accident nearly four years ago and since then I suffer from chronic sleep deprivation. This app is helping me to fall asleep as well as helping me go back to sleep as I wake up throughout the night or when I have episodes of nightmares. So far I have only tried the soothing nature sound Audios.

I've never successfully meditated before I tried Calm. After the very first try, I could do it and I felt such a peaceful feeling that it was indescribable! I've been practicing every single day since I started and I feel so much more calm and focused. I can now see what everybody was praising meditation for! If you're a nonbeliever like I used to be, try it. There's a full week of free trial period. Then you can decide. üëç

My first meditation was for a body scan and it was a blissful experience. It lasted 11 mins, not too long or short. I enjoyed the tone of voice of the narrator. It felt like an outer body experience for me. I just finished my second meditation w/ Lebron James about managing your emotions and it was truly helpful! I already love it and will likely keep doing some meditations until I feel content. I will likely invest in this app for a year. Good job creators!

The best app ever. Actually works makes life that much calmer. Me and my family enjoy this app because it teaches how to be still, how to be calm, and how to just focus on breathing. We are now able to sleep through the night wake up refreshed and ready to take on the the stress of our daily lives. We all need to use this app because it really is brilliant.

Such a great app! It gives us different choices depending on how we feel and what we need. Whether a night story, nature sounds, smooth music, master classes, breathing exercises, general body exercises. And then we have meditation, where we can choose different topics and also narrators. Absolutely love it! Special compliments for "Commuting" (perfect for everyday ride) and "Daily Calm" (every day a different topic). Well done!

definitely the best meditation app out there. it's not just blindly meditating, you can find a specific course that fits for your goals. there is so many options. this is the best app I have downloaded, and 1 very great decision. I have worked on fixing so many problems I have had with myself through here. I would suggest buying the 1 year plan. for just I believe $60 you can have all of these amazing outlets to better your life. peace, love, and serenity you all ‚úåü§ô‚ù§

A lifesaver for loud office spaces and restless nights. I use the soundscapes during the day to help stay focus on my work and not to be overwhelmed by the noise in my open concept office, and I use the sleep stories at night. I have not been able to make it through a sleep story yet, I fall asleep within 10-20 minutes (that doesn't happen without the sleep story).

Calm has helped me considerably in learning how to root myself in the present moment. It has really taught me the meaning of mindfulness. I have learnt how awareness can be the first step towards narrowing down your attention for accomplishing something. It has really been a pleasure to learn the wonders of meditation with Calm.

Well worth the price of entry. I suffer from insomnia, and between meditation and the sleep stories on the app, I am have fewer medicated sleeps and more natural sleeps. Strongly recommend for anyone in a similar situation. You won't pick it up and have it click in over night, but over time, you will feel and experience the difference.

Worth the money to me. This is just a spectacular app. If you're struggling with stress, trouble sleeping, tension, anxiety and other "shtuf" this app is a great way to learn coping tools, relaxation methods and much more. The breathing coach alone has drastically improved my bedtime "unwind", work stress, driving commute stress, LIFE stress. I use the breathing tool multiple times a day. This app is seriously amazing. Definitely has made life CALM. ‚ù§Ô∏è

Paid for the app so I would be forced me meditate everyday (or most days!) with the fantastic Daily Calm. It has worked! Have also accessed the excellent Jeff Warren 30 day programme. Am now doing both everyday. Haven't used the music or stories. Also really appreciate the app tech - such a good, reliable, intuitive app; a pleasure to use. It's beauty also helps. Refreshingly glitch-free. Tamara must work very hard to produce the Daily Calms but they always sound fresh and genuine.
Only did the 7 day trial, but I enjoyed it. I liked the relaxing stories and music, but the motivational speeches were also good too great

This app has been a true lifesaver for me. The sheer variety of sessions available with the full access is accommodating of so many different mental health issues. I initially started using this app as a way to help me sleep which worked really well. There are plenty of background sounds to choose from and the voices are lovely to listen to. I have since been using the app to help with mental health and it has been a true life saver. If you can pay for full access then I highly recommend.

I accidentally bought this app for a year and It ended up helping me get through my daily life. It has a series on how to meditate that helps you find your own sweet spot, it has a lot of other types of meditation also. There are sleep stories where celebrities and meditation enthusiasts read a relaxing story to you, there's even a music selection that is relaxing and a mood check in. I love this app!

Very wonderful app. Centers you around interesting topics to keep you mindful of not being anxious and restless and keeping you relaxed. Great for meditation. Authors voice is soothing and relaxing. Many different musical songs as well to listen to for relaxation including waterfalls etc. A relaxing story is given daily to put you to sleep.

I struggle with sleeping and the sleep stories have helped me tremendously! I have yet to listen to a full story, and that's ok, because I'm sleeping! I start every morning with my mindful meditation, and I can tell when I skipped it. I also use the breathing exercises before heading into a meeting, or dealing with a difficult situation - this practice helps me manage things so much better. Best investment I've made!

Fantastic app. My husband suggested it for my insomnia because of the sleep stories - which have really helped tremendously! I've also started using the meditations to relax during the day. The guidance through the meditations is just right - not too much or too little. I like the fact that I can choose different background sounds (or no sounds) while sitting the meditations.

As a newer parent dealing with a crying baby all day can set my teeth on edge and not make me calm! Which doesn't help with her sleep, or my sleep. Today for the first time in 3 days I was able to remain calm during putting her down for her second nap. Not only that but she fell asleep!!! And then, üòå I feel asleep. I feel incredibly restored now. My baby and I thank you!

I don't want or have many apps on my phone. I'm am so very happy with this one! I highly recommend this to EVERYONE! I helps with dealing with my anxeity and insomnia. The stories are great, but for me the breathing/calming sessions are fantastic. They help my mind settle so I can get to sleep. Thank you Calm team! Much gratitude to you all!

I've been using this app at bedtime with my 6th grade son and it's great! There is so much variety in the soothing sounds, bedtime stories, inspirational readings, music and beautiful scenes. I really like the breathing exercises. The visual is very intuitive and the tones allow you to close your eyes. You can choose between 4, 6 or 8 breaths per minute, and up to 60 minutes total. We've just touched the surface of all that's there but we really like Calm.

I love this enough to give 5 stars! At first I expected it to be one of those apps that gave you pretty much no free material but I was wrong. For free you get enough to actually want to use app. The sound quality is amazing also. I'd love to be able to afford premium but for now as long as the free content stays this great, I shall not be uninstalling.

This app is amazing. It is so helpful when I'm feeling stressed, nervous and or if I just want to feel calm and relaxed. You would not believe the options you have when it comes to listing to music, audio stories, and relaxation sounds. Oh and the video / picture variety is amazing. If you're reading this you should definitely get this app.
great app to unwind and relax

I have no problem paying for an app that serves me well. I've tried various guided meditation videos and free apps but I love this one enough to pay. I prefer having so many options in one place. I don't know how I ever survived without the sleep stories! I'm finally maintaining a daily practice and getting better at mindfulness. I've become much less reactionary. If you're just looking for a quick, mediocre meditation, go to YouTube. Otherwise, this is a fantastic app and worth every penny.

Very calming and inspiring app. I love the daily guided meditations, there is a new one every day and they are short enough (10-12 min.) to squeeze into even the busiest mornings or right before bed. There are also longer meditations and self-improvement courses for when you have more time (up to an hour, I like to listen when I'm taking a walk or doing some freestyle yoga) as well as meditation timers and sounds for self-guided sessions (my wild brain needs the guidance, though). Overall, love!

I downloaded this app to help me fall asleep, but it has already begun to do so much more for me. Not only has it become part of my nightly routine, but it has become a hub for self growth. I love the different areas & focuses that help me be intentional throughout my day. & at the end of my day, the daily check-ins are a place where I can reflect and set my intentions. Plus it's exciting to have new daily plans uploaded each day.

Love this app! The Daily Calm meditation, the sleep stories, the music plus the numerous targeted meditations make this a must have for me, multiple times everyday. I feel much calmer and more focused since using Calm for the past two months,for example, I've actually finished two fiction novels in the past week, which I haven't been able to do for years due to anxiety and lack of focus. Meditating really does work wonders, and this app has it all!!

I love this application. I love the guided meditations and encourage anyone with anxiety, depression, and other medical issues to develop an open mind and lean towards holistic personal body and mind approaches conjunctive to your medical treatments. Don't be afraid to try new treatment options. My health has improved drastically practicing my exercises via CALM. Many different applications towards meditation can be found, but, I personally love and chose CALM.

Very calming, I use it every night. I always listen to the same story but it makes me fall asleep in 5 minutes. I also only have the free version and there is about 5 free stories maybe 4 on them but I'm okay with that. I think it's a great app for calming people and helping people fall asleep.

Best collection of meditations out there. Narrators are very good at talking in a softer manner. Worst thing when you are trying to focus is to have a jarring voice pull you out of your center. Have not found a single narration like that. Used this app for a few years now.

Great application. The meditations I have tried have two parts: first there is a talk that can help you see and understand new nuances of the topic, and the second type is the actual guided meditation. I have most liked body scan series. It helped me a lot to identify that I am actually tensing a lot of parts of my body when I am stressed and helped me relax both my body and mind.

This app has been a game changer for my students and me. We are able to take the time to breathe, refocus, and enter each day with a calm and positive mindset. I highly recommend this app, and I think that everyone can benefit from taking a few minutes each day to be mindful and present. I also find the sleep stories a huge help when I find it difficult to settle my mind at night. Love Love Love the Calm App!

A wealth of resources - too many to outline here. They include meditation instruction, guided meditations, and many helpful short courses on everything from managing anxiety to help with eating problems and sleep difficulties. Lots and lots of stuff, everyting I've tried had been both sound and sensible. All in all, a most wonderful resource. If you don't know it, it's well worth a try.

I originally downloaded this app a few years ago when I was going through a period of particularly bad insomnia (I was sleeping 2-4 hours a night most nights, and some nights I couldn't sleep at all). While it didn't cure my insomnia overnight, it did help me feel more at peace with living within such uncomfortable circumstances...and eventually I did learn how to fall asleep. Years later I still come back to the app in phases. Lately it's been helping me find calm during the COVID quarantine.

I just LOVE this app. My preference is the reality based ones, however my friend who uses Calm as well prefers the fairytale based ones. Each to her own! Since starting to use Calm I generally find I've missed most of the story as I'm asleep in a few minutes. It's a rare night I need 2 stories. My biggest regret is that I sometimes forget to rate each story after I've used them as I wake up next morning and close the app. Keep them coming please, you are my sleep salvation. Cheers, Chris XX

I love this app. My free trial ends in 2 days and yes I will pay for the service. Why? Because good things are worth paying for. The idea, the development, the marketing. A good product is available because it costed money to create; and it will only survive with consistent cashflow. Calmness takes time to learn and develop, with consistent practice it can become a natural being. But for those who chose to whinge about the cost rather than seeing the benefits - you just will never get it.

This has really helped me through a tough time. I'm sleeping better and am much more relaxed in daily life. There are many different options for sounds, songs and themes of meditation and I think that everyone can benefit from a little peace in there life. I heard about this app from the mindfulness documentary on Netflix which I also highly recommend.

Along with Headspace, Calm is my favorite method to enjoy guided meditation! The app has lots of variety and guided playlists for what you'd like to focus on. It keeps track of time meditated, sessions completed, and how many days (streaks!) you meditate in a row. The option to switch between female and male narration is a neat feature, and for $60 it's hard to beat for a year subscription! I'll continue to use this as my platform for guided meditation, and recommend it for daily use and your meditation/mindfulness goals :)

Great app, well worth the annual cost. I was skeptical about the sleep stories, but they really work! The music and soundscapes are a brilliant tool for blocking out background noise in the office. Have and will continue to recommend to family, friends and colleagues.

I got the free trial to test out because all the great reviews on this app. Any app that has a free trial and charges you after the trial is up i cancel the subscription immediately after i sign up for free trial. I know i canceled it but something went wrong somewhere because after the trial was up i was charged $74 or around that price. not a good time to get a charge of $74 especially when they failed to charge my paypal account 3 times before it went through. Not happy

Works like a charm! I have used this app daily for several years. My children enjoy the sleep stories, especially Stephen Lyons, and I unwind in bed with the Daily Calm each night. Several years ago, I used the daily mediation to help me get through the loss of a loved one.

Totally worth the $70/year price. I love the options and the daily is always spot on what I need to be working on in my recovery. I have never spent money on Apps...ever.... Until this. A friend had it, and we used it daily....and I had to get it for myself.

I absolutely üòç this app!! It can be difficult for me to power down my brain at night, but when I use the app I fall asleep almost immediately. I use it for naps, too, and wake up so refreshed. My two favorite aspects of the app, though, are (1) I actually learn neat things from some of the stories, and (2) I resolved years of flight anxiety in just one trip using the flight anxiety series and that has been a priceless benefit. ü§î What about Idris Elba for a story??

I love this app. It ensures a peaceful outlook for the day in lieu of jumping up and running. Set up a distribution to my girlfriends list to share as often as possible.This is helping me to acknowledge the importance of honoring mind,body and spirit daily.It also reminds me that if I Don t feed myself first then there really is not much to give others. Taking time for you demonstrates love of self something different from selfishness. Thank You for this well thought out app that is helping me change my life.

This app is wonderful! It's easy to navigate, is chock full of great meditations and tools - even for beginners like me - and I'm growing everyday in the practice of meditation because of Calm. I feel like Tamara Levitt and I are besties bc I start each morning off with her 10-minute meditation. When I am having trouble falling asleep the sleep stories work for me. I have gifted this app for 30 days many times, and it's by far the most valuable $ I spend each year. #soworthit ! TY Daily Calm!

This app came to me at a critical time...not sure how id be getting along without it. Id been tossing around the idea of coming up with some kind of mindfullness/meditation regimen that i kind implement on a daily basis but had no idea where to look, how to start, etc. CALM has met that need and gotten me really excited about having it as a daily tool moving forward. Its been an absolute Godsend. Huge help for those in recovery I can say as well.

Early returns- this is far and away the most useful 'leisure' app I have on my phone. The guided meditations are spot on and the music selections are wonderful (super stoked to see Sigur Ros featured). My OCD leaning, anxious personality is already showing some softening with only a handful of days into one of the many anxiety focused programs. This is a phenomenal app, and I'm excited to keep progressing further into it's offerings.

The moments of meditation are soothing and reminders of how we can take care of ourselves. The softly spoken voices on this app give serenity for those moments along with pleasing nature sounds or music. There are also bedtime stories that will send you peacefully into dreamland. The stories are read by familiar voices and you will find it hard to get to the end. This app very gently reminds us how to take a little time daily to practice self-care and breathe.

This used to be one of my favorite apps that I recommended to all my friends, family, and patients, but they stripped away what used to be free content and now what is left is useless. I'm the opposite of calm now... update: Thank you calm for fixing this issue. I now have access to more of the melodies and love the app again! Use it daily
replyContent: Hi there, I apologize for the trouble accessing Calm Music! A mistake was made when these programs were locked for you. These programs should now be unlocked moving forward. Reach out to support@calm.com if you're still having trouble accessing content.

content: The One for Me. Having tried several other mindfulness apps, I chose this one. It's simple, easy to use, has lots of options including meditation, bedtime stories to help you sleep better, music, master classes on different subjects, a variety of background sounds to choose from, and even body care - stretching sessions. The daily mindfulness sessions are 10 min in length and Tamara's voice is very pleasing, adding just the right touch to my experience. Try this app !!

I meditate frequently and have used several different apps. Calm is still my favorite. The meditations themselves are very helpful especially the 21 days of calm. I enjoy the attention drawn to thoughts and emotions as things naturally part of our mind and body and the need to step aside from them, observe them, tell them how they're serving/not serving us, and breath through. The meditations are smart as they explain a bit before diving into the meditation itself. Love Calm üôèüßòüíú

wonderful. I tried Headspace, which was ok but for some reason Calm was more appealing to me. I have not missed a day in the last 30 days since purchasing the app. I'm a first time meditator and the impact on my life in this short time is already evident. I have actually lost weight and am doing nothing differently except being mindful of my habits. I have more concentration, and a new hope that I am in control of more of my mind than I realized. thanks Tamara!!!!

This app is changing my life. I couldn't come back to mindfulness practice for last 2 years, I've been eaten alive by depression. I've decided to use Calm to try to come back to my practice. I remember it helped me a long time ago. And you know what? It's amazing! Calm has everything - meditations (wonderfully guided), music, sleep stories, series of classes and body exercises! Really everything! And Daily Calm series keep me excited about my practice and I can't wait to hear the new ones!

Love this app. It has really helped with meditation and being in the moment. Sleep guided meditations are fabulous. I use them everyday especially when trying to go back to sleep, which has always been the most difficult to do. Still a long way to go but so grateful bto have this app help the journey.

This is the first app I've written a review for, and I'm doing it because I think the quality of the meditations is substantially higher than head's pace, with more variety and better structure. Loving calm and the price is very reasonable for the constant utility it provides on a near daily basis. Kudos to the team.

I've used the sleep stories in the free app for about a year. I love Blue Gold, but none of the others. I have enjoyed hearing new stories since signing up for Premium. I prefer the male voices - more soothing in my opinion. A few days ago I started listening to the meditations. I'm enjoying therm, and hope to stick with it daily. My audiologist suggested I play the background scene sounds during the night for my tinnitus. My husband enjoys it too. I tried the sleep sounds but find them annoying.

This app is truly wonderful! No more sleeping pills for me, this app puts me to sleep in 10 min or less. I also use it during any type of stressful situation, and to soothe my fear to flight for wich they have an excellent meditation session. It has so many things, bed time stories, and more. Meditation for kids as little as 3 years old, I can't wait to show it to my baby !! Some people complain that there is not free trial. but I can assure you, it is really worth it, you won't regret it.

This app is so unique! It's fits everybody's individual needs. Me, as a individual, love this app and I always seem to keep myself balanced by using it. I have adhd, bipolar etc etcetc. But I really feel at any stage of my stability, if I look and search anywhere on this app, to how I'm feeling internally, in the moment, it really releases and helps me and has helped me for maybe 2 or more years. My go to, my core, my gratitude, I would love to be part of this, heal the world ‚ù§Ô∏è

I can't believe I'm about to spend $60 on this app, but I really think its worth every penny. Im on my last day of my free trial and I really love it and am ready to pay for it. My favorite part is the bedtime stories. I've had sleep issues my whole life and have tried almost everything. The stories get my mind to stop spinning in circles and the voice and sounds are relaxing. Nature sounds and white noise are great, but they are not enough on their own to slow my overactive brain. Great app!

I wasn't sure at first if this app would become my new habit and actually make me want to use it without feeling like it was just a chore... however during my short 7 Day trial I have truly wanted to use it more and more and I'm actually noticing a difference already in my behavioural and mental state throughout the day. There are so many resources that I'm also starting to see are tailored just for my specific areas of concern and I absolutely needed that. I think I üñ§ It.

AN ABSOLUTE GAME CHANGER! I can't say enough about this app, ironically I first purchased it by mistake (I'm a broke college kid and it costs about $70 a year). However since purchasing it for the first time a few years ago I now make it a point to budget for my annual charge. This app helps me sleep soundly and has given me the tools and space needed to tackle my life-long struggles with OCD and panic disorder. I am now more happy, focused, confident and self-aware thanks to the Calm app team!

I absolutely love the Calm app it has something for everybody in my family. I absolutely love meditating it's a part of my life that I do every day before my family weights and it helps put me in such AIDS then and calm mousse for the rest of the day. My daughter is so obsessed with the sleep portion of this app she loves all the stories and she can not sleep unless she listen to one of her favorite stories. I also really enjoy the master classes that's just an added bonus to me. #familyfriendly

I love Tamaras soft voice and the app helps me so much to bring a structure to my daily mindfulness which I was struggling to acieve on my own. I also use the bedtime stories sometimes which are so relaxing that i have never managed to stay awake long enough to hear the ending of any of them. I also like that there is a daily theme and message and i look forward to using the app every day, sometimes more than once a day. Keep up the excellent work!

I love Calm! Every night I listen to a bedtime story. One problem, I rarely hear the end of the story because I've drifted off to sleep.üò¥(I've even listened to them when I'm wide awake so I can find out how the stories end!) I also use the guided meditations for pain management (just getting over a broken arm) It has really helped. I couldn't be happier with this app. Sometimes I just stop and Breathe and whatever is stressing me out just melts away. Wonderful!

I LOVE the Calm App. It has been my constant companion during a difficult time and has made all the difference in allowing me to sit with my emotions and embody a mindful approach to each day. The sleep stories have allowed me to get into a much better sleep routine. There is always a new topic to explore. I wouldn't be without this app ever again.

Great app. Wouldn't be without it now. Used the free options then decided it wasnt too bad for the money and benefits I was getting. If my minds being busy I use a sleep story so I'm busy listening rather than thinking. For general sleep I pick a sound like rain or washing machine and if I need a wind down I go for a guided meditation. Full app is definitely worth it for me. Never glitches either üëç

this app is freaking amazing! It seriously has everything I need to help me be mindful every single day. I have had it for about a month and I am still impressed by the amount of content and all the range of topics/issues covered. They even have content specifically for kids. I put on one of the night time sleep things for children when my 7 year old couldn't sleep one night and all 5 of my kids were listening to it and said that it made them drift off to sleep. Pretty awesome.

I am learning to be present and at peace through this App. It's a work in progress but one that I look forward to expanding on each and every day! I have found that I do not feel quite "right" during my day if i have not taken the time to meditate. I am grateful to the Team who created this App and work hard on its growth.

Wonderful soothing voice coaxes you through a relaxing session of calm. It helped that I was sleepy üò¥ but it would have been relaxing at another time. A soft spoken voice is often a great help, if you think of a child & there response to a gentle voice. To me it's a key that unlocks my calm. I just need to reach for the key more often. I feel I've found a new path to calm.

Excellent app! There is nothing that comes close that I've ever been made aware compared to Calm. More choices in the numerous categories offered that one would never imagine. It's far from an app that you will know within 5 minutes of your choices. It's truly amazing what you will see. ‚ô° it ~*~

A lovely app. Can't afford the premium version at the moment but I'll sign up if my fortunes change. For free content I have access to the 1st session of each 7day meditation - I'm sure it works better to do the whole week, but the 1st sessions are still helpful on their own. There's also a good selection of free natural sounds & music. I love the sounds of the ocean to relax and get to sleep. And the breathing bubble exercise is great when stressed & can be edited to suit the person. Perfect!

fantastic app for anyone who suffers with stress, anxiety or any form of mental health problems. I always wanted to try meditation but wasn't very good at turning my brain off. This app has taught me how to meditate correctly and changed my whole outlook on life. I would also advise people to upgrade to the full app as there are some great bits on here for health, body and children.

I tried a book and it just didn't click. Then I looked at classes and they were $50 a month. After reading reviews online about the various apps I decided to try this one for free. By day three I was hooked. I found myself looking forward to the next day during my 7 day session and I always found time to squeeze it in even if it was right before bed. I'm no expert, really barely a novice, but I have found this app extremely helpful with introducing me to meditation.

I use this app every single day to meditate, sometimes I just do the Daily Calm for 10 minutes, other times more. There is a meditation for whatever my mood is. I'm going on my second year and the effect is noticable. I used to also use the sleep stories quite often yet find now they lean more towards children's stories. I hope they can add more variety.

love love love this app. Has helped me immensely. The sleep stories and sounds are so pleasant and peaceful. Even the scenes are beautiful to listen to while reading a book or drifting off to sleep. Definitely worth paying the subscription. keep up the great work calm and thank you ü§ó

Worth the money. I was nervous to pay this much for an app, but I have begun to use it almost everyday. I also use the kids section regularly and can not believe the difference in my kids. When they start to lose it and I want to yell over the chaos, I turn on this app instead. I make all my kids sit on the couch until the meditation is over. At first they treated it like a punishment üòÇ but now they know they're going to feel better without me screaming. I also give myself timeouts. üôè‚ù§Ô∏èüëç

I am an experienced yoga and meditation practitioner and I have found this app very pleasant and supportive. The meditations are well written and delivered beautifully. Thanks for the wonderful app! It would be even better if we could have a few longer meditations (building up to 20, 30, 60 mins). I love Stephen Fry's voice! This app is well worth it! Dealing with anxiety and some postpartum, and just an overall hectic life, I was desperate for a positive change to improve my mental health. This app delivers that. I use this app first thing in the morning, when I'm at work, to go to sleep, and especially when I begin to feel anxious and overwhelmed, it calms me, and brings me the sense of peace that I need to make it through the situation.

When I cannot shut my mind off from the worries of the world to the worries in my life I turn on this app. It just takes me away. I sleep better all night if I start with a story. I have used this during the day to destress. I have told my friends and my clients about this app. There is a variety of voices and stories to choose from. It has really helped to destress.

The enormous selection of content (music, sleep stories, meditations, etc.) allow me to remain calm and comfortable throughout my daily routine. I suffer from social anxiety disorder and in my short time of using Calm, I have found the content to be extremely helpful. I was recently told that I will be the Master of Ceremonies for my friend's promotion to Technical Sergeant in the USAF. I am hoping that practicing the content here will apply to this situation and that I get through it.

I love the Sleep Meditations, especially Deep Sleep with Tamara Levitt. I use them nearly every night. The other meditations are helpful too. I plan to make more time for them in 2020. The mindfulness meditations on Anxiety, Stress, and Forming New Habits are especially helpful. I highly recommend this App. It will not only grow with you, but will also challenge the user.

I have struggled for more than twenty years trying to find a meditation practice that suits me; one that feels like a gift to myself, rather than a chore. Calm is that practice. The shorter daily meditations have been a gentle, enjoyable way for me to ease into the idea of stillness and presence. I am incredibly grateful to have found this app.

Amazing app! I had this app as a gift and still on my yearly gift certificate - this is the most impact any app has had on me. Now, it's been a slow burn, I've used this app time and time again not thinking it's made a difference but I now find myself incorporating meditation into my everyday life when I feel anxious, as a default I go to it. The narrator has such a calming, uplifting voice. The app speaks so much common sense and focuses on acceptance and compassion of what is and who we are. Persist - 5 *s

I was a bit sceptical when I first got this app nearly a year ago. I tried a few meditations but my busy mind just wouldn't allow me to relax. I've been a poor sleeper for around 30 years and thanks to this app, I am now getting to sleep within 15 minutes whereas I have spent many sleepless nights in the past. I'm due to fly to the other side of the world in a couple of months and I will definitely be using this app to relax me on the long flights.

I absolutely love this app. I wish it wasn't so expensive to unlock the other apps or the other parts of it but this app has helped me tremendously. The breadth of options in this app is impressive. Being rested and calmer let's me deal with life stressors with clearer thinking and better follow through. Meditations are short but so helpful throughout the day. Thank you, Calm.
Very nice. Lots of options. Even if you are just trying it out, they allow quite a variety to sample!!

I love the app, its ease of use, the friendly sounding narrators, and I really like the pictures, nature sounds, and the music, as well. It really makes meditating much easier to incorporate into one's daily routine. Thanks for a wonderful app, keep up the great work!

I have bad anxiety and pressure everyday. This is why I downloaded this app. You guys came up with the perfect idea to calm us beings down. Thank you....

It is a wonderful app all theme way around. I would like the option to choose a male or femalevouce for each meditation. I love the quotes at the end. The ability to mark the one that spoke to me to customize my meditations. The nature and graphics soothe. The options are delightful.... Enjoy!

I love this app, I use to relax, meditate and sleep. I've not upgraded to the premium but I do wish there was more free sleep stories to try first or a longer period of a free trial, 7 days to try it all is not long enough. It's one of the best apps I've tried and I've tried a lot.

Really useful its been helping a ton. It's great step forward to bettering yourself without breaking the bank. Really enjoying the app! As cheesy as this may sound, this app is changing my life, day by day. I bought the app after a week and I am very happy that I did. This app has it all! Meditate, Sleep sounds, stories, etc.! The Daily calm is the best, I listen to it every evening before bedtime and it puts me right to sleep. Can't go wrong with this app and the layout and scenes are so realistic. Great job!! I would give you 10 stars if they let me

To my mind, the annual subscription is very good value for money when compared to the cost of one to one councilling.

I love the sleep stories. They really do help me fall asleep. Thank you for the work you do. I tried the free version of this app for awhile and I've been paying for it for several months now. i love it. it has everything you need all in one. sleep stories, soundscapes, meditation, breathing exercises, and reminder functionsnif you forget to take those few minutes everyday. 10/10 would recommend.

Wow, this app is fantastic. You can adjust the volume for the background music. You can choose readers depending on their voice style. The meditations are fantastic, especially the one for sleep. And I love the deep breathing feature... everyone I share it with loves it too!

Having experienced anxiety and depression for huge parts of my adult life, the meditation sessions on this app specifically from James Warren have really helped me understand how to cope with stresses of daily life. Absolute god send - it's not a quick fix, you have to practice and practice and practice as you would with anything , then all of a sudden you start to realise they benefits

I love the daily 10 minute meditations, the "scenes" both for their images but especially the nature sounds or music. My daughter (7 treated old) loves using Calm app. On me, it helps clear my mind throughout the hectic day and definitely at the end of a stressful day (or night, if you work nights).

Ok, love the app so far and last week it was therapist approved! Thank you for creating this mini electronic haven. I had never been able to meditate before until I found Calm. I now make meditation part of my daily routine, and Calm makes it easy.
