I highly recommend it for everyone , as I have found meditation to be so helpful in calming anxiety & depression, and showing me how to be truly present in the world!

It has helped me through bad times ( spouses cancer) and busy stressful times. I am a caregiver (RN) by profession and the breathing exercise is great and easy to do during my break. Hands down, THE BEST app, worth every penny! I listen to all the features. Sleep stories to Masterclass, nature, music, soundscapes...I love all of it! I would like to say I have had great success with this app. I have PTSD and getting to sleep has been a constant struggle. Nothing was working I tried the calm app for 6 day. This app is true to it's name. Calm. I've tried a few different meditation apps and have often struggled with the orators voice. I have paid for similar apps and CALM, in my opinion is the best of the best. Can't live without this app. I use it, my kids use it. I had the free version for a long time, and the kids still use it. I have a lot of trouble getting to sleep and staying asleep. I've had this problem for around 13 years. calm is brilliant and really worth the money. It's the only app that's worked for me and really helps to stop my anxiety from taking over so I can actually drift off. I use the sleep stories section the most. really useful xx

I started using almost a year ago amd I love it. I live only 3 miles from the beach but not close enough to hear the tide--a sound which soothes my soul. pretty intense my first time meditating..nice app

This app completely blew my mind. Not what I expected, yet better. I am not on the Premium version, yet I have access to great content, helpful content. I love the stories. I can get in bed and have someone tell a story as I fall asleep, like when I was little. This app is great the meditations are very soothing and always helpful! I was just recently told I suffer from quite severe anxiety. Calm has beyond exceeded my expectations. very effective and affordable for the quality narration and sound effects. I really like this app and using it to bring calm to my stressed life and frazzled mind, leaving me able to rest and be peaceful through it all. Every time I use the CALM app sleep sessions I fall asleep before they even finish! This is a huge breakthrough since I usually have insomnia. I have also been using the meditation sessions and feel more in tune with the present. I definitely recommend everyone should try this at least once!

Amazing calming app. Can be used for sleep or for mediation. Anything. You can play your music from the app and go on other apps and it won't stop. Which is an amazing feature. Some stuff is to pay for. But I love open minded mediation. Just allows you to do so much.

I'm absolutely loving this app and everything it has to offer! My daughter is 3 always had hard time sleeping. I'm loving the Mastermind classes, calm body , how to meditate and all the different musical and soundscapes. I feel calm, at peace. less stressed, more energy, more Patience and mindful

if you need some relax how are you want to come you can download this app and after that you will feel that this app is for you and this app will help you that no one can ever give this type of calmness and relaxation ever

I shopped around and this is not only the best one I tried, but they have informational sessions and sleep stories as well as meditation series and a new one daily. there are guided meditations for all ages and occasions. This app has helped me stay grounded through stressful moments. Noticing when panic and anxiety surface and being able to calm the mind when it does is amazing. This is a skill that is well needed. What an awful app! I did the free trial and it would not allow me to cancel and has now charged me for 1 year subscription! I cannot find a number for customer service and it will not allow my message to go through about my complaint! Beware, the free trial is not free!

This is the first app that has actually worked for me so far. Simple short meditations that you can extend because the app has nice background music that plays as a default. I've been using Calm for a few weeks now and it's made such a difference! The most relaxing, soothing sounds and voices. Instantly calmed me down in 10 minutes, Max! I seriously was taken to Zen mode! Calm is A very powerful mental tool that combines physical suggestions with mental escape techniques for the perfect mind control over anxiety, stress, insomnia, or over active mind where you just can't shut ur brain off when the body is trying to enjoy comfort and relaxation mode. I feel very in control and empowered after my sessions.

I love everything about this app. For a small fee per year its given me more joy, peace of mind, insight and serenity that I would have thought any app could. The daily content is lovely. It's a great return on investment and I would happily recommend it to everyone.

Calm has been a lifesaver for me. It taught me how to meditate and helps me stay on track. The wisdom is priceless and incredibly validating to how I'm now trying to live my life every day. I can't praise this app enough! I only wish there were more master classes added more regularly, I love those. Anyone that's dedicated to learning how to meditate, can find that here.

It's something I find myself going back to over and over again. Not like most apps that I struggle to stick with. Super easy to listen to. A great needed time out in my day. Loving everything they offer. Getting so much out of this app. So worth it.

A little gem of an app full of useful features and excellent content. It offers so many options to utilize mindfulness and meditation for everyone. It has some of the best tools I've seen for those who experience problems with getting to and staying asleep. It is fantastic as a teaching tool for using meditation to manage anxiety. I am a mental health professional and highly recommend this app. I've given it as a gift and feel it is worth every penny.

Great App! Helps me sleep and meditate with ease. I suffer from Anxiety and this App helped me find my Zen after a few weeks of using it. I've used the breathing montior more than once especially during my anixety triggers and its helped me calm down way quicker than trying to do it on my own. Highly recommend to anyone suffering anxiety!!

I really love this app. I use it for myself and my children. it was well worth the yearly price. I wish I had jumped on the discounted price offered a day after I started the free trial. but I do not regret paying the full price either. it has helped my anxiety tremendously. I have used it now for over a month and have zero negative to say about it.

By far the best App I've ever had. Beautiful content that helps me so much with anxiety and general relaxation. I also love the stories that are available in the sleep section narrated by beautiful voices such as Eva Green. I couldn't recommend it more!

This app is helping me find my calm. It has guided meditation beautiful stories and music to sleep to, and lots of choices. You don't have to do it all to get benefits just use the bits you need for today. I am really enjoying the peace I feel by taking ten minutes or so just to focus. Thank you creators
I can get sleep and do good in school

I use calm daily. I recommend this app all the time to stressed out mom's, like me. It's a simple way to learn mindfulness since each day has a new 10 minute lesson. My kids adore the sleep stories. They listen almost every night and I use them as well when my mind won't settle down. They are great for quick pick-me-up naps, too.

very good..easy..seamlessly navigate around the app for your own unique CALM experience..I've had the full app for a few months now and even though I thought for a while before purchasing because the cost put me off a bit ,I needn't have worried ,the app has helped me and my family a lot...thank you to developers for a great app....5‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê's

The 1 star reviews kind of scared me, but so far, this app is amazing, it has music for sleep, that can play even when your phone is turned off, and so many other great features there are to explore. The app is already so calming and helpful, this app is 100% worth it, it's absolutely free, so I say you give it a try.

Fell in love with this app right away! First time I used it I was at work behind my pc with hundred or more people around me. There was so much noice and discussions, phone calls going on... I decided to escape trying out this free trial CALM app and still to be able to work at the same time listening relaxing music or meditation. It worked! I am glad i found sthing that helped me not just through out stresful work days but also to find rest once i made it home! Thank you for this! Ivana

The app is full of resources. The sleep stories, music and meditations are wonderful. A fun feature I wasn't expecting was the master classes. I LOVED learning about sleep and how to begin getting better sleep. This was a game changer for me.

Calm is an amazing app, even if you only use the free version, they still have useful tools that you can use on a daily basis to help keep you grounded and focused on the present or whatever you may be searching for. I do highly recommend the full subscription though because it's a fair price if you struggle with concentration or just need an escape from every day life and it unlocks so many different features for you to utilize. Plus it's cheaper than a therapist!

Life changing! This app literally helped to reduce my anxiety which was interrupting my sleep almost every night. I'm learning how to meditate and let go. I love the short stories at night. They really do help me to fall asleep, and I'm now more relaxed, focused, and positive. I no longer worry about things that I have no control over. I love everything about this app! I highly recommend it!

The stories, the meditation and the sounds have all helped me gain a clearer mindset. Calm has been by far the most understanding and tranquil apps I have used to help ease my anxiety and improve my sleep over the past few months. I would highly recommend it to anyone seeking peace from listening, breathing and relaxing.

Tried the free portion every day for 5 days, and then bought a yearly subscription! 5 bucks a month for peace and understanding any time of day? Yes! I tried other relaxation, meditation, etc apps and i like this the most. Covers alot of areas of life, and has storytelling as well.

Despite our differences this app seems to have worked how to navigate the complexities of our individual neurological wiring to enable each of us to find a way to self awareness and well being at any age or gender. It just keeps on getting better and better the more times we use it. Grateful we have Calm in our life and for all the amazing people behind it.

The absolute best app for sleep, rest, yoga or meditation! I've had a few app issues,but now everything seems to be working really well! The sleep stories are wonderful, and the scenes with sleep sounds are just beautiful. I purchased the subscription for the premium services. It's worth it for me!

My favourite app, i am very reliant on this app, i can not aleep without it. Had problems after the last update but after writing about it here the developers had it fixed straight away! definitely worth the subscription. thanks Calm. Just paid for my 2nd year and I have listened to it every night! Alan sklar is my favourite. Love his new one that last an hour and a half. Would love an option to have the stories on all night, maybe on repeat or one after the other. Thank you so much Calm,
replyContent: Hi there, I'm so sorry for the trouble! We've released a hotfix (4.11.3) to resolve the audio stopping issue. Reach out to support@calm.com and we'd be happy to answer any questions!

content: Calm helped me a lot especially during those times that I was anxious, nobody to talk with, desperate. After praying I would start with calm and it felt like God talks to me through it, too. After that experience I know that I needed the app. Calm helps me calm my nerves every time. It reminds me to breathe... I can't just tell you how many times I've cried with this app.

I came for the meditations. I stayed for the sleep stories. Despite being physically tired, my mind loves to be active and stress about things when it's time to go to bed. Focusing on the relaxing stories has quieted my busy mind and allowed me to drift off to sleep instead. I especially like the space travel and train ride stories.

Calm is aboslutly wonderful, I live in a disfunctional family and I feel like I am the only sane one apart from my grandparents. And I have been listening to this for 12 hours, and I love it! It really takes the stress away my favorite is Water flow. I usually listen to the calming music then the story books, cuz I don't wanna pay 69 bucks for a month

Great mindful app I downloaded in conjunction with my current CBT course. I chose to pay for the yearly subscription which I felt was very reasonable & worth every penny!! I have yet to take advantage of everything available as so much choice - music, stories, mediation!! Have been trying to do the daily calm every day & find it very relaxing - it is important to take time out of every day for yourself!! Thank you for this app üíûüòäüíû

It's an amazing app! I bet that with premium it's even better (somehow), but if you don't really have the money for it (like me), it's still most definitely worth installing if you need to relax after a long day of hard work and constant stress. I really recommend it!!! ‚ù§

Just what I need. Ive got to get in the habit of using it everyday because I find myself all over the place. Especially after work. I work in a Hospital at Customer Service, Volunteer Services and Comfor Suppot There is always something new I have to learn. Two days are never the same. That's not including my personal life. When I get home I've got to learn to leave work at the office and take better care of myself, if nothing but five minutes. Caml has helped me so much. Thank you.üåπ

I was given an opportunity to use Calm as part of the Calm Schools program. I've been working my way through the kids offerings to see what will work in my classroom. I've really come to love the large selection of things I can use for my insomnia as well as the Calm body stretches. Would definitely pay to keep the app.

Works so well- lots of different options especially for beginners. I was never able to meditate before and now I find that if I don't do it on a daily basis, my anxiety comes back. The app has lots of different options whether you need a quick 3-5 minute mediation session or a full hour one.

I purchased the yearly subscription of this app about six months ago because I love this app. I use it almost nightly to relax my mind and fall asleep. It works so well that it is very rare that I actually listen to a story entirely because I fall asleep within minutes.

The Calm app focuses on mindfulness. I have been using Calm for four years; I struggle with chronic pain, depression, PTSD and anxiety. I had insomnia but use nighttime meditations and sleep stories when . I love the 3 minute emergency calm for high anxiety situations. There are master classes for mindful eating, creativity and overall healthy living. I do the body stretches. I love the relationship with self and relationship with others series. I have learned how to breathe again b/c of Calm.

I love this app! I use it every night before sleep as well as during the day before work. It has helps you focus and grow into better, more mindful person. Definitely worth the money. Also, I like Tamara Levitt's voice. She's very relaxing.
Not sure why it's listed as free. It's about $60/year.

Its a good idea to create this wonderful thing cause this is what we need the most in today's world. Only one problem is that without unlocking calm premium u don't get to hear many records. Only couple of them are present. Otherwise i love this app.

This app is worth every penny and I am a fan. The diversity and quality of the choices is great. My path in meditation has started here and has helped anxiety and stress. if I can not afford next year I will use the trial because I need this helpful tool to maintain my balance. Thanks

My family uses this app in multiple ways each day - sleep stories (including kids), daily meditation breaks and themed series - we have genuinely used them all for a few years now. A great way to being mindfulness gently into your day. Oh, and Tamara's voice is one of the most soothing things I've ever heard!

Instead of looking at Instagram or watching a show of Netflix, I put a sleep story on and fall asleep MUCH faster than I used to. Plus, the sound of rain falling plays once the story is over, so you don't have to turn the endless play of episodes off in the middle of the night.

Perfect for kids and adults alike. I originally purchased for myself but found the kids section and thought I'd give it a go. Now my kids (7yrs and 9yrs) beg for a "sleepy story" every night and sometimes when they want to chill during the day. Even the hubby loves settling down at night with a sleep story. The masterclasses are brilliant and insightful too. It's a fabulous app. I've recommended to many a mummy with similar results too.

I really do love this app! What more in the world could you ever want than Stephen Fry lulling you to sleep every night talking about the origins of lavander? I refuse to pay the crazy amount of money this app is. Don't get me wrong; I do understand the reasoning behind the cost. So I simply listen to the only free one every evening. Blue Gold. About 8 months later I still don't believe I have ever made it to the end.

So far, so good. Just downloaded the free version and tried my first meditation. I've never meditated before but always wanted to learn. The quick introduction was amazing. I feel way more calm. Am a bit worried about other reviews that say the "free" part doesn't include much. In today's world, a lot of people don't have extra money for apps, even if they are good ones.

i haven't missed a day listening to calm since I discovered it 48 days ago! I've been sleeping better and feel more relaxed. My little 8 year old grandson loves the stories. Sometimes he will come to Grammy's room when he can't sleep to listen to calm. Or sometimes he enjoys listening to a story while riding in the car. It's been really sweet to spend time with him in this way.

This app has helped me tremendously. I suffer from anxiety and depression and my doctor recommended meditation. Tamara (the narrator) feels like a good friend at this point. There are bedtime stories that I just love and help me relax enough to get to sleep. When I wake up in middle of the night I start a new one. Thank you so much to the developers of this app, you're really helping me help myself for a better today and brighter tomorrow.

I love this app, especially for helping me sleep (insomnia.) The relaxation and healthy lifestyle "master classes" are great and just the perfect length of time to fit into a busy life. The topics are relevant and relatable. I discover something new every day and new content is added regularly. I'm so glad I tried it out!

I love the purpose of the product and the content is very good, however, the design of the app is not very "Calm" and reminds me a website design with Flash. Also, the number of email marketing sent is quite high for what it is supposed to be a product for relaxation purposes.

This app is wonderful. It encourages me to meditate everyday. It has a variety of meditations (for sleep zzz, self-care, stress relief, mindfulness), soothing music and sleep stories. They expand their portfolio The narrative voices are beautiful. I am very happy with Calm - it makes me happy:)

Now that i figured out how to pay monthly, this app is my favorite thing ever. I've struggled with insomnia or off-cycle sleep my entire life. Ambian, six melatonin, NyQuil - none of it feels as good as drifting off to one of these a bedtime stories. It's SO relaxing!! I fall asleep within ten minutes and I feel way better in the morning and throughout my day. I totally recommend this app.

I love this app! I've only done a few sessions but it's brought me so much calm and inner peace already. I enjoy the "daily calm", and when I'm working I listen to the "rain on leaves" background sound to help me focus. I haven't noticed any bugs yet. Keep up the good work, Calm team!

I have trouble sleeping and I first tried headspace and you only had 2 songs that you can listen to for free.Then when I found about Calm I loved it. They have alot of songs that are free and the songs and stories are amazing. I really love this one song called "The Ocean's Lullaby" and it helpes me go to sleep.Best calming app I ever tried.

Their customer service is AMAZING!!! My sister downloaded this app without my permission and I was charged $59.99 and they refunded me my whole money back. Elza is so kind and so sweet she helped me get a full refund. Plus, I looked at this app and I noticed how much positivity this app brings, and i wasn't angry at my sister for that and she could have downloaded anything but she was drawn to this app. Its an Amazing App and their customer service is top notch!!!

I recently received a FitBit as a gift. I've been wearing it while I sleep and my sleep feedback was upsetting. I realized I have to make changes to improve my sleep. I use Calm meditation to help get to sleep and it is helping so much. It can't be understated how stress affects our health and how important taking time to meditate and breathe is to learn how to handle it better.

I tried quite some apps before. With Calm, I like the quiet ecosystem that we can tap into early in the day, late at night, it is there for any moment. I love the meditation with Jeff. None before were quite right for me. This time, I am looking forward to learning new concepts and practicing them with Calm.

This is my go-to App at the moment. I love the short daily calm meditation first thing in the morning, the selection of music is beautiful and the extra bonus of bed time stories, even my 8 year old daughter is using the App. Thank you, it's wonderful.

I am addicted to CALM. Having so many topics and types of meditations available in one app has helped me be more consistent with my meditation practice and is helping me go deeper. I particularly love the many options for playing background sounds or music during the meditations or just anytime. I was skeptical of the bedtime stories but when I use them, it really is like a lullaby that helps my mind shut down and go to sleep. Thank you CALM and Tamara Levitt!

I have been using this app for over 2 months now and It's awesome. Best guided meditation and mindfulness app I have tried and have tried many in the last few years. I have seen positive results in my mindfulness practice, increased concentration throughout the day, improvement in my quality of sleep, increase of energy throughout the day, reduced worry and anxiety and overall mental health. Give it a try.

I absolutely love the Calm app. I have been able to fall asleep faster, and get better quality sleep, when I use the app. Meditation is so healing. I'd recommend this app to everyone, if I could. I paid for the annual membership as an early birthday present to myself. I don't regret it one bit. Well worth the price! You guys do an amazing job. Keep it up!

I cannot sleep without something in the background. Calm has these soundscapes, my personal favorite being the babbling brook, however, it doesn't stop there. There are audio books on meditation and mental health, and (seemingly) fantasy stories to help you fall asleep. I have yet to check it out, but what I have seen so far is amazing. I highly recommend it.

This app is very nice! The support team is very impressive and I am happy giving 5 stars because it does what it says it does! If you're attracted to meditation and the multitude of relaxation methods then this would be for you. It has lots of stuff included in the free version as well. Well done guys üôÇ

Awesome so far!! I have only listened to the free sleep stories, but they are extremely well done. I have not experienced a meditation in the form of a story before, but it works great. I don't think I have lasted more than 10 minutes using them to get to sleep, so I had to listen to them again in the daytime just to see if there was any story line I was missing.

I appreciate the variety of meditations so much. The sleep stories have also brought so much calm and comfort to my evenings. I never have to worry about sleepless nights and tossing and turning again. This App is a priceless investment in yourself and your well-being.

Excellent Idea For An App! Spot on! I wanted better sleep so I selected the Sleep portion and skipped the rest. But before I could use it, I was pondering on whether this would mess me up. lol And make me pay 70$ to fix it. Just the thought gave me a panic attack... . I had to go back and get it... . Then I got so depressed about not having better control over my emotions, I got the the rest while I was there. Let's hope this works! they dont have one for Addiction.... . ... lol

Enjoy the free version. I wish you still offered access to teachers. As a principal I have many teachers who are overwhelmed and are struggling. But i still refer them to the app., even the free options have lots of benefits. Thank you. I have really needed this for the last month.

By far the best meditation and mindfulness app I have ever used. And the year long subacription is very cost friendly. My favorite option in this app is the night reading/unwinding/ calming. I havent found one so effective. I also love they narrator choices including some soothing voices of well known actors/actresses. A+++

I've used a couple of different apps, but found that I love Calm the best. Their guided meditations are amazing, and have helped me to further explore what/why I'm doing it. The music has been instrumental in helping to drive my focus with the recent craziness that is the world. Can't recommend this program enough!

I love to listen to sleep/motivation meditation and calm masterclass like Elizabeth Gilbert. It help me to overcome my psychosomatic. I prefer calm because Youtube have too many ad in the middle of the video nowadays. While I like the calm and soothing way from most of the narrator, I wish you can also add excited or energetic meditation session or energetic masterclass from narrator like maybe Tony Robbins to boost motivation and positive habits of thinking. Thx team!

I love the stories and mindfulness lessons. The music and atmosphere is also enjoyable. One downside (not worth losing a star) is that my notifications don't seem to work as a reminder everyday, but I still use it most days. I'm definitely happy with my paid subscription- completely worth it!

Hands down this is the best app I use for meditation. The sleep stories, music, images and of course the guided meditation is all a win in my book. And the fact that Calm continues to add new content so that the app never gets stale, it's worth the price of gold to achieve Calm in one's life. Keep the content coming!

One of the most important lessons I've learned of late is the significance of mindfulness. Calm helps guide me each day as I learn to control my thoughts and acquire more focus through meditation. I truly recommend it. I not only feel less stressed out but, in being more mindful, when stressful situations arise throughout my day, I am more apt to handle it better and not be thrown off. I live the background sounds i can choose like rain or waves and there are great audio walkthroughs!

A beautifully designed but simple app. Can't believe how much of the content is free. Lovely narration and music too. I will be using this a lot. UPDATE: I have found this helpful and inspiring so I've subscribed. Not something I do very often!

Best App Ever I would give Calm 10 stars if I could. After just the second session, I could feel a change in myself--definitely for the better. I am learning how to relax, and I love it! The session narrator has the most soothing voice and I really enjoy my daily meditation. Calm really helps me throughout the day, and to unwind and fall into a deep, restful sleep at night. Can't say enough good things about this app. You need this in your life!

I have used this app for several years and it has constantly developed and perfected not only the app itself but also the range of tools to facilitate my process of sleeping, calming my mind and thoughts and also educating me with the fantastic masterclasses on offer. I particularly like that there are new daily calm meditations every day so there is no end of variety available. I also really like that the meditations are categorised so I can search and find what I need when I need it. Fab!

I use this for the sleep story time narrations because I have anxiety that I'm working to overcome. The people who read the stories are so soothing, their voices are like chocolate. I haven't finished the end of a story because I fall asleep within about 10 minutes. Thank you to the wonderful people who created this app! Well worth the price to have full access to the stories
so far it's been amazing I've always suffered from anxiety and ADHD but this app has helped me open myself to a whole new version of myself thanks so much

Insightful, varied content, something for every occasion. I particularly like the structured courses, and the music (which helps concentration at work). It's been very helpful for my anxiety and depression and I recommend it strongly.

This app has not only helped me with my insomnia, but when I was in the hospital for a month for a fractured spine, it helped keep me calm and literally saved my sanity! Now my husband even uses it to bring down his blood pressure NATURALLY!!!!!

I love this app because it helps me with my Anxiety , Depression & Panic attacks . Plus it helps me with getting my clients to relax while I work on them . There is one other one that I do use and that is Liquid mind . But I do mixes them up and my clients love listening to both of them . So Thank You making this app it is well worth the price keep up the good work . Now if you could get " Liquid Mind " on here that would be " Fantastic " !!! Thank you Rich The Massage Therapist .

I love this app! I use it throughout the day. It helps keep me centered with meditation, music, and it lulls me to sleep at night with the sleep stories. Only thing is I never get to hear the whole story. The narrator's voices are so soothing. I do love this app!

I love the choices of calming music and ambient sounds. I have just completed my first meditation and I am actually feeling emotionally better. I would highly recommend this app to anyone suffering from anxiety or depression. I can not express in words the way this app has helped me cope with the stress of daily life.

this app has really good content and is lovely to use. The only thing that makes me somewhat uncomfortable is that a lot of the techniques of mindfulness are based on vipassana (and possibly other meditation systems) and these are part of deep spiritual practices- so I feel that this should be acknowledged and grappled with somehow.

Calm, is the perfect morning, afternoon or evening ritual that helps provide balance to an otherwise stressful day. Whether it's listening to a sleep story, the calm of the day or just listening to the in app music, Calm will renew your mind and help you better appreciate yourself and everyone around you.

Love it! I've yet to make it through the 25 minute trip to the lavender fields of Provance France. It helps me stay calm and not get panicked when I put on my cpap, darn irrational fear. Just wish there were more free stories and stuff for those of us that need this app but can't afford it. $70 is a lot on a fixed income.

I write this after doing my first nurturing session and I feel amazing. I've never tried anything like this before, I saw a commercial on TV and I got Interested. The user interface is great and I'm excited for my next session tomorrow. Give it a try invest in yourself !

Great app for anyone getting started on their meditation journey. Easy to use and very approachable for newcomers. I've been using the app consistently for 3 months and have noticed improvement in my mental health and feeling of well being. The narration is excellent and the additional app features (sleep stories, music, stretching, etc.) are a noce bonus.

Calm has been a fantastic app for both myself and my daughter. It has helped with bringing mindfulness and focus to my day so I am present and living in the now not worrying so much about tomorrow. The "sleep sounds" has helped my daughter get to sleep at night which has been difficult for her lately.

This app is truly wonderful. I have downloaded and also purchased many apps in an effort to aid and improve my meditation practice. These applications usually had an area where it was effective but this is one of only two I can recall that has put together everything I need to meditate. The developers put a lot of thought into this application.

I love the diverse options Calm offers for meditation (open, timed, led, breathing, short, long, and in depth themes if you want to get premium). The pictures with inspiring quotes at the end of a session are a motivating factor, as is the keeping of data (and streaks) that the app does automatically. These elements of Calm are all helpful in trying to build a habit of meditation.

Absolutely love this app. I used to have trouble turning my brain off at night and would regularly see 5-6 in the morning before I would fall asleep. This app is a total game changer for people like me who have insomnia. Love it! I've already recommended it to several friends! ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê

Beautifully designed app and a great way for me to start my meditation practice. So much to choose from and new stuff being added all the time keeps things interesting. Would love to see more meditation around creativity, focus, etc in the future.

Thi app has helped me a lot! I suffer with postpartum depression, depression, everyday stresses, Etc. The stories really help calm my nerves, and I love the meditation. I really like this app. It has also helped me to fall asleep the past few nights which is a big plus

I definitely LOVE this app. It is so tranquil and soothing. It truly serves it's purpose in calming me spiritually, mentally, physically & emotionally... I especially love the music and the speeches... Thank you all for your hard work and effort to calm us.

Absolutely love this app! My husband and I use the sleep stories to fall asleep, and so does my 7 year old who struggles to wind down. The Focus music is perfect to keep me productive during the work day. Worth every cent I paid for the full version.

This has been the best gift I have bought for myself. I look forward to each session and feel better after every meditation. My son and I both enjoy the sleep stories and I've used a number of the other features too. I am so grateful to the Calm team for creating this app. Keep up the great work, I can't imagine life without this app now. ‚ô•Ô∏è

Love this app! All I need to say is that its helping me learn how to relax an focus on the present moment. I have the full version am I don't know what I'd do without this app every night but also through out the day as well. So many options an different choices. Cannot even express how much I love this app.

absolutely wonderful app, remove Instagram, remove Facebook or Snapchat, and let yourself go with Calm, you will be forever grateful. The narrators, the sound, and the teachings are beautifully made. I highly recommend it. This should be one of the best app on this store.

The app is fantastic and has helped me massively over the last year. I listen to it most nights to help me unwind and fall asleep. I also did some meditation before an interview to help me feel relaxed and confident - I got the job. Couldn't recommend this highly enough.

Literally change my life. Had never meditated before and was super skeptical, but the 21 days of calm series was a great introduction for a novice. Almost 1,000 sessions later and I'm still loving it. I appreciate that they regularly add new content based on user feedback.

its a great tool to have :) its worth every penny! i downloaded it on the advice of my therapist to use when im feeling stressed or anxious. sometimes you just need a moment to gather your thoughts and de-escalte and this does it for me. also the nap stories are the greatest! i dont even know ive fallen asleep until i hear the birds wake me 26 mins later lol. honestly best app out there!!!

I really love the stories and meditations from the Daily Calm app. I've been using it for over a year and I find it helps me reset when my day gets too crazy. This app always works and I've never had any problems with it, even with my 3 year old phone!

I love calm, I originally downloaded the free version as suggested by my GP to help me sleep and it has become my lifeline. I have been using the app for 3 years now it solved my sleep issues! I have also found the other meditations, calm body and masterclasses amazing tools that I use as part of my daily life now. After the success of the free access I now pay for my annual subscription and it's worth every penny. The app continues to grow and get better all the time. Please keep growing ‚ù§üßò‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

Excellent app to learn how to meditate or use if you regularly meditate. It's easy to use and versatile with its guided meditation and timed environmental sounds meditation. I've been using this app for several years and I see how my meditation practice has improved over time when I look at my meditation profile statistics that details my meditation frequency, total session, longest streaks, etc.

This app has literally changed my life. Mindfulness meditation is a fantastic practice, and Tamara Levitt and the Calm team make it approachable and easy to get in to. Though I'd tried Headspace, I definitely prefer Tamara's voice and meditative promptes. A year later, I'm incredibly grateful for this app.

Very helpful with managing adult ADD and anxiety. I'm only a few weeks in, but I've been able to commit to doing at least 1 session every day, which is crazy bc I've never been able to commit to something for that long without skipping a day or getting bored. I'm proud of the progress I've made so far with this app. As long as it's available, I'll continue to use it.

After creating your account you'll see a blue page with purple bottom says 'Unlock Calm'. On this page, at the bottom, it says 'Try 7 Days Free' inside an oval that says 'CONTINUE'. Underneath that, it says '$59.99 per year after FREE 7-day trial'. IF YOU DON'T WISH TO PAY FOR A SUBSCRIPTION, click on the 'X' on the top-left hand corner. DO NOT CLICK ON 'CONTINUE'. I have not paid for subscription but even with it's limited selection for non-subscribers it's still great! Hope this helped.

Provides a wide variety of options for your chosen purpose: to relax, fall asleep, achieve "waking sleep" states for creative purpose, teaches meditation... - all with awesome background sounds. It is definitely worth exploring the 7 day free trial to decide if it would be useful for you.

10 STARS! I started off only using the meditation cues to help me relax during a stressful time, but recently I have found the sleep stories. Those are life changing. It relaxes me so much that I am out in seconds. There are even nights when my husband cannot sleep and he asks for me to turn a sleep story on. I also love the kids section, I plan to use it in my classroom to help my students calm down on the days when their energy is through the roof! ABSOLUTELY IN LOVE!
Full version gives so many options to find calm and relaxation. I find it helps me be more centered.

I really like the length of meditation sessions this app offers. It is very convenient if you are busy or don't want to spend more than 10 minutes a day practicing mindfulness. The sleep stories are also a great feature with a variety of readers. I didn't think I'd like any noise when I go to bed but actually it's been helpful.

Excellent app. I recommend it to all my friends. Great guided meditations, love the background scenes and the bedtime stories are great. The premium subscription is expensive for an app, but a good investment for your well being.
Love this app, wish it didn't have ads or didn't cost so much!

It's still early on, but I know this app has helped me to relax. Practicing meditation through the Calm app every morning has kept me calm and far more relaxed throughout the entire day. It has also helped to give pause and new ongoing perspectives on how to deal with anxiety.

I love Calm! It's great whatever stage you're at, experienced or a beginner. There's so much to choose from whatever mood you're in. The teachers are excellent, the pace gentle, the effect remarkable. I try to use it every day.

it really helps me sleep. I do the quick check in before bed to get out all my feelings and worries and stress and settle in for a sleep story and they put me right to sleep. I struggle with turn my mind off so I can sleep and these stories are the perfect calming thing to focus on because they are calm and interesting but I'm not so engrossed in the story that I have to finish it. I often fall asleep within about ten minutes and I sleep deeply all night.

Calm is one of the best apps on the app store for meditation it really lowered my anxiety level. There are sleep stories to help you fall asleep and I love them they work every time. You do have to pay to have full access but I think it is totally worth it I love everything about this app!

I'm new to this app, and have not explored it completely, but every bit of the content I have enjoyed so far has been very well done. I feel like this app can help me change my mindset for the better. As a busy person, I have always had trouble relaxing. I think this may be the key, or at least a map to a good path.

I hesitated to spend $60 on the subscription. It seemed like a lot for an app and I'vewasted money before on apps I thought I'd use and didn't. But I truly missed this after the free trial, I use it regularly and I've never once regretted the cost. a highly quality and useful tool for improving daily life!

I've had insomnia for years and took Ambien, melatonin, etc. to fall asleep. Once I discovered bedtime stories on Calm I haven't had to relie on sleeping aids. I fall asleep 90% of the time and actually stay asleep instead of waking up at 2 and desperately trying to fall asleep again. I'm hooked and use Calm almost every night. I enjoy their selection of storytellers. My only complaint is that Calm has only one meditation person who sounds like she's addressing a class of kindergarteners

Amazing app for meditation and relaxing. The teaching sessions are great as well. So much content to choose from depending on your mood, emotions or needs at the time. The subscription cost is also way less than other popular mindfulness apps.

This app is wonderful! You can tell that real people actually put time and work into it. It's not just an app with a collage if meditations taken from different places. The different levels and the choices I have for meditations, sleep storys or even calming meditations for my kids are amazing!

This is a fantastic app - I read some reviews before using it and personally, the annual subscription fee is so worth it. There are a wealth of options to support me learning meditation and to apply in different contexts e.g. when in pain. The Deep Sleep meditation is very helpful as are the Sleep Stories. It has helped me to start building my meditation muscle and help me be at peace in a very difficult time of my life.

I have the subscription version and love all the features. I feel it is worth it. I don't use it near enough but when I do it helps reset and rebalance. The music, meditations, stretches, everything!!! Love it!
I use this,app every day. It has great features, especially the music. Well worth time spent.

I am really excited about using Calm, it is a wonderful tool to work with in my everyday life. I highly recommend it to anyone who wants to find a way to engage in meditation, mindfulness and quiet the chatter that is in our minds, with Calm you will find how to be centered, peaceful and at ease also you will discover many ways to help you handle every day issue. A world of possibilities right in the palm of your hand will make you feel better and happier, healthier and wiser. Love it üíñ

I'm a beginner and have tried a couple of meditation apps previously and never stuck with them, generally feeling they're disjointed in the sessions and not consistent enough to hold my interest. Calm was reccomended to me and I'm hooked. Calm IS different. I'm really enjoying the quality, consistency and realness of the sessions and feeling the benefits already. The content of each session makes sense to me, is non judgmental and real, making this new journey I'm on easy and enjoyable.

I'm thoroughly enjoying using this app. The daily meditations are instructive and a great way to give yourself time and self-care. The app includes a variety of guided meditations as well as music and sleep stories so there are many choices to suit just about everyone! ü§©üòçü§ó

Really like Tamara's voice and calming demeanor. The sleep stories are great for a rejuvinating afternoon nap. I have used this app for about 3 months and made it an early morning practice to begin my day. It sets the tone for the rest of the day

I have the free version of this app, and I use it weekly. I love the background sounds and music I can use to meditate on my own, but the guided meditations are also beautiful. Haven't checked out much more, but I grateful for what is offered for free. Great app.

This app is a blessing. I've been using it ever since my therapist recommended it and I absolutely love and am thankful for their quick relief of anxiety. The new feature of writing your 3 gratitude is great as well. Although a bit pricey I do ultimately think it's worth it.

Love this app!! It's a sanctuary for the restless and stressed. Helps you slow down your mind after a long and hectic day and calm the endless stream of thoughts. The scenes are my favorite part, especially "evening crickets" and "summer meadow". I've literally fallen asleep just listening to them.

I love the variety, soothing background sounds, and the calming voices that narrate the sessions. I had subscribed to a different app, but I had to get the Calm app instead. It is worth every penny! I have yet to explore the entire catalog of meditations, but I am very impressed so far.

I have found Calm to be really helpful and relaxing when I'm feeling anxious. The daily calm meditations have lots of variety and are well structured. I have used many of the other practices too including some of the sleep stories though I'm hoping they will add some more of the longer sleep stories! I tried headspace but it's so expensive to sign up to that I went with Calm instead. Overall I think this app is the best meditation one I've tried for the price, but it is still a bit pricey.

It's so nice to fall asleep to a story every nig'ht and Tamara Levitt's morning meditation is part of my daily routine. The only issue I've found was when I wanted to upgrade to lifetime member and could not do it. I could not find a phone number anywhere to call for support. Other than that, it's SOOOO worth it!

I've used a few similar apps and this stands out as the best. Originally picked it up for the sleepcasts, which really give me a quality nights sleep. The meditations are great, especially the 7 day series. Content is regularly updated so there is always something new to listen to

Really enjoy this app... The content is always being updated and the reminders to breathe and meditate each day help me stay focused. Tamara Levitt is such a soothing person and I am grateful for her commitment to mindfulness and help starting your own practice. It's absolutely changed my mindset and the way I react to stress and conflict for the better.

I love the customizable sounds while meditating. I personally love the rain and the chirping birds. The master classes are wonderful. I usually listen to those on longer car rides. Daily exercises plus you can choose specific meditaions for things you need to work on or if youre feeling a certain way or going through a situation.

This app is life changing. It takes mindfulness to a new level of accessibility and ease. I only wish you had a monthly subscription package along with the yearly one. I hope one day your incredible content will be available for non-English speakers as well. All the best. Also, Tamara's sessions are the best!

Music, meditation and sleep stories galore! I love the calm app I appreciate how much its eased me into the routine of fitting in a 10 minute mediation every morning to give me a mindful and relaxed start to my working day. It has destresssd me and has helped underpin my own ability to become aware and control the stress before it takes a hold. Matthew Mc Conaughey reading me a bedtime story üòç.

I love calm! It helps me fal asleep every single night. I've set this "Bedtime" So it notifies me when I should go to sleep! There's tons of stuff to use for falling asleep, or even relaxation. It's got sleep stories, music, Lullabies, guided meditation.. and SO much more! The only thing I think I don't like is that a lot of the music is blocked cuz you need to buy Calm "Premium" Or something. But all in all it's great for sleeping, and meditation, or helping you relaxüòäüòäüòå

I use the sleep soundscapes to go to sleep every night. Also really enjoy the daily calm. I've found a lot of good meditation techniques through this app and think I've become a lot more mindful by using it. Love it and definitely think it's worth the price.

Calm has honestly been a life saver for me. I work in a stressful job and am a full time grad student. I do not have a lot of time for myself. Buying the full version, which I love, gives me more resources and reminders to create a little time for myself. It's a little pricey, but to have access to more resources helps me to process events as they come, versus constantly worrying.

This app has had a very positive impact on me, at least my Family has mentioned more than once how much more Calm and mello I am. Instead of reacting abruptly to most of my daily challenges I now take pause and really think how something is really going to effect me or others. There are few other features to this app besides meditating that I really enjoy, like the sleep stories, music/sounds/scenes, and the many self help series. I highly recommend Calm.... give it a try!

I have used this app to help me calm down, to fall back asleep and just on a daily basis. It has changed my life. Sleep has been a long standing problem for me, not anymore. Now as soon as I am aware that I have woken up and am struggling I open the app and either pick a sleep story or a body scan. Let's just say I never remember the end. Thank you Calm!

Only had it less than a week but love it so far. I love the music and the relaxing images. The meditations are great, the voices aren't annoying, and there is so much choice of what you can do. Even yoga videos! I will be purchasing it at the end of my 7 day trial.

I almost didnt purchase the app because I thought it was too expensive for "just a phone app," but I'm so glad I did! The content and usefulness is SO WORTH every penny ‚ô° If you're on the fence, definitely give it a try!

Great features, amazing program for schools - The fully unlocked program is versatile for many situations and easy to use. I like that the music is regularly updated. I'm lucky as a teacher I get it for free through Calm for Schools and think it's really forward-thinking and responsible of them to expose the upcoming generation to mindfulness. The only drawback for me is the limited # of meditations with John Armstrong. I prefer his voice and love the option to choose between male & female.

Very happy with the app, I'm beginner and tried free versions of calm and headspace before deciding on c mainly because I preferred the voice, ambient sounds and found the beginners course worked better for me. Very happy now with paid version extended beginners course. Only thing that was better in headspace is the falling back to sleep meditation, so I kept that. Only negative point in calm is the ambient noise is too loud on night mode, not sure if I can actually change the settings.

Does what the name says, very calming. I love the music selection. I used it to help my little ones sleep when we were on vacation. I like how there are so many options to choose from. Sleep stories, breathing exercises, stretches and calming music. Nice app!

Absolutely essential during crazy times like this, though I've used this app from years. When I first started traveling a lot for work, I would be restless and miss home. I would use the app to help me relax and get to bed. Now that I can't leave home, it helps me to stay focused and grateful for what I have. I can't recommend this app enough.

Life changing. I love this app. I use it for daily meditation and sleep, and sometimes I listen to thunderstorms or humpback whales just because I like the sound. I started as a total beginner and have been hooked since. Great way to help you sort out thoughts and emotions and just accept things for what they are at that particular moment.

I really love this app! Since I've been using it I'm getting better rest at night and my stress levels are much lower. I love the sounds and music and I use the sleep stories often. I'm always out before the story ends. This app is so great and user-friendly. I would definitely recommend this app.

For someone who does experience a lot of stress and often anxiety, this app allows me to take a second. It eliminates my focus from any stressors and allows me to decompress. It really calms me down. I enjoy the daily calm session. It's the perfect amount of time to just sit and exist in the moment.

I only use the sleep stories on the app. They have greatly aided in helping me fall asleep. I enjoy that you can select stories by category and that new stories are often added. This is one of the few apps I pay for and it is well worth the money.

Ever since I've underwent my Healing session not too long ago and having go through a family counseling, it's thanks to this app that things are a whole lot easier for me. Even if I don't have the dough to purchase the whole selections of Meditation sessions, I still owe it all to this app, and my Sister for introducing me to the world of Meditation.

Very well desinged app, which helps me with my daily practice. I use the free Meditation, very nice ‚Äúgong‚Äú sound which marks the end. Also other nice features like the daily quote, the backgrounds. Only negative point: it needsa lot of energy so that u need to recharge my mobile sooner

I love that I don't have to think about what meditation to do as there is a daily suggestion. However, I can choose to do a programme as well to address a particular issues. The sleep stories are wonderful if I'm struggling to sleep and need a calming distraction.

This is my favorite app! I fall asleep so much quicker each night now that I have a routine and typically only make it 10 minutes into the sleep story. On my own it's so much longer. I enjoy the daily calm and sometimes I just listen to the rain.

I have struggled with insomnia for about five years. The calm app has helped me get back to sleep when I wake up in the middle of the night which is wonderful. It has improved my quality of life. The Calm app has also been helpful to calm my anxiety, so I can continue to do the work I love, creating and maintaining a large highschool garden so students can have a place to relax and breath deep with the butterflies, birds and plants.

I love this app bc i can learn about and apply the concepts of meditation with each session. The meditations are always easy to settle into. I was introduced to this app by a therapist friend. It's been the perfect tool. I've been wanting to develop the practice of meditation for a few years and this makes it easy. I highly recommend it.
I use it daily! I can't stay away through the sleep stories and I love the "Drifting off with Gratitude" guided meditation.

Brilliant app - have fallen asleep many times listening! Incredibly good for relieving anxiety. Lots of different options and the kids stories have helped my 7 year old relax and fall asleep (still haven't got to the end of the velveteen rabbit!) Worth every penny and more!

I have been interested in learning to meditate and have goals to help alleviate anxiety and depression. The guided meditations have been a useful tool by introducing me to the world of meditation. I have felt a noticeable improvement in my overall health. I especially enjoy the sleep section of the app. It helps me fall asleep more quickly and aids in the quality of my sleep. The Calm community is a wonderful and supportive group. I would highly recommend this app to anyone! Thank you Calm!

I love Calm. It is the whole package with the meditation series, music, sleep stories and daily sessions. The user interface and support is amazing. I signed up for the annual subscription and it's totally worth it. I'd totally recommend it to anyone looking to improve their focus, sleep quality or reduce stress, anxiety.

Love Calm so much works for all the Family. Helps me so much with my anxiety and stress. my 6 week old baby who has reflux, I use the music section and it helps calm her during the witching hour. My nephew loves the sleep stories and my oldest son and partner listen to the sleep stories too. It such a life saver that I did buy the subscription as it is worth every penny. Not sure what I would do without it if I'm honest, it has helped me through some dark times and also the good times

First app I've ever paid a subscription for - totally worth it! missed it after the 7 days of free trial and very glad I got it back. Morning routine of meditation established! Sleep stories are priceless. PS: READ what you sign up for (7 days of free trial then automatically charges you) and you won't have to give 1 star here just because you forgot to opt out.

Calm is exceptional! Covers a variety of topics, daily meditation, mood (quick way to identify your mood, record notes to yourself, and offers options for addressing that mood! The master classes cover a variety of topics. The variety of approaches (music, stories to help you go to sleep, new meditation daily and meditation for specific purpose no matter what the subject of a meditation, class, it is always presented in a positive way. Using Calm has improved my practice 100%!
I find the Daily Calm a wonderful way to take a moment each day to simply relax and reset. I also find the other meditation helpful in easing stress and boosting self esteem

I have only been using this app for a few days but I really enjoy it. The daily calm is beautiful, long enough to have a relaxing effect but not drawn out too long. The quotes are lovely, thought provoking and inspiring. The other sounds are gorgeous also. I have not yet used the stories. Calm is the best meditation, relation app I have used so far! I love Calm!

Calm is a source of peace in my life. I like the variety of the content, the inspiring quotes at the end of a meditation session, the calming voices, and keeping track of my practice on a calendar. Also if I need a background sound to concentrate, I can listen to whale noises or cat purring, among others. I only wish that the nature imagery for every background sound to be HD. Some of them are blocky.

I have been a user of calm for almost a year now and I love it. I enjoy the free meditations and look forward to a point when i can pay for the newer stuff. I love the level of expertise that is shown when guided through the meditations. Almost always as if on que they say exactly what is the best way to reign things in. Love it and reccomend it. Edited 10/10/19 i did have some issues in March...
replyContent: Hi there, I'm sorry for the trouble! Reach out to support@calm.com and we'd be happy to look into this for you.

content: Best mindfulness app hands down imo and ive tried a few. Geared towards sleep issues, depression and anxiety. Has a kids section. My 7yr old does a meditation every night after story time and it makes a massive difference to help get him off to sleep easier. Great sleep stories for adults (even got a Stephen fry one). My boy loves ' big bad woolf learns anger management' lol Great value for money, cheaper than headspace, ive been telling everyone about Calm and giving out many guest passes.

Calm is hands down my favourite app.. I use calm at least once if not twice a day. The guided meditation allows you to easily follow instructions without feeling overwhelmed. This app is helpful if you deal with anxiety, have trouble sleeping, have panic attacks ad great for kids. I love this app!! Absolutely worth it!!

This app is amazing, really helped me take a different perspective about my problems and life in general. Guided meditations always suprise me with how they hit right in the target. At first I used the free version and then upgraded and I think it is really worth it.

Plenty of features from sleep stories to meditations and music to exercises. This is a whole package and it's tied together nicely with a great interface. After a few days of the 7 day trial, I was happy to pay for the full year's subscription.

This is so great. I love thunderstorms, wintery winds and remembering the loons on the lake. This app is free for 7 days, I wish I could afford the app for all the time because it is so worth it. I highly recommend you try this. Calm the kids with stories too.

Good for beginner or experienced mediators. One is able to program background music and environmental sounds. You can create a medetation routine to wake and go to sleep to that suits your schedule. The atmospheric music can help sets my day on a positive note. I can use the music for teaching yoga class and for my healing bodywork practice.

I think it is perfect I just think it would be smarter if I paid in advance before sampling anything thank you very much for your time keep up the good work update I've been using this app for over a month between the holidays friend committing suicide disabled husband terminally ill father in law I will say that the Calm app has kept me Steady. also leading me close to my spirituality. calm is my favorite app in the entire Google Play Store good for all ages keep up the good work calm.

Calm always helps me find peace and stay grounded. I use it in the morning to start my day off and at night to drift off to sleep. I have my children listen when they are having trouble sleeping and send them the inspirational messages for their day too. The calming sounds and voices help me so much to meditate and release. Love it!

Love the app. Chronic insomnia 30+ years and sleep meds generally don't work. Add Calm sleep stories and the odds of my getting to sleep increase remarkably. And if I still can't sleep, I have wonderful stories by amazing narrators to enjoy. So many different voices and accents.

I love this app and I wish I could give it more stars. It helps me calm down and make me happy with the nature sound, and the app definitely brings you to your happy place! Definitely get this app because you will have more happiness if your life because of it.
This app has gotten me through so much darkness. I am overwhelmed with love for the creators and the readers as well. Thank you from the bottom of my heart!

There are daily meditation with inspirational quotes, sleep stories, yoga, breathing techniques, development of a peaceful state of mind that is stronger and more resilient. Also included are kids activities and stories in addition to brain training so many resources for guidance to a better day in many ways.

I've always used meditation to help with my stress and my diagnosis with anxiety and PTSD. This app has help learn new skills to help cope with all of those things I deal with it has wonderful and all different kinds of beautiful meditation guides to help you thru, also just beautiful meditation sounds to do it yourself and relax the music and stories are so great as well I love this app. I cant wait to see what else they do as they grow this app into a healing journey for everyone who needs it.

Been using this app since I saw my fiance meditating with Calm over a year ago. I personally listen to the narratives while I drive on the way to work or while I'm doing simple chores; I don't traditionally meditate, but I enjoy both the daily meditations and longer series a lot! Even though I get the Headspace app for free from my employer, I never use it. I pay for Calm because i like it so much!

Fantastic app! I love the variety of guided meditation topics, the section for kids is fantastic and i the music section is really great. Being able to download my favorite meditations and the calming music/soundscapes to my phone before taking a trip was very helpful so i could access my content without needing wifi. I also love getting the daily reminders with quotes. Definitely worth the price.

Great app. I have a 17 day streak, that is the longest I have ever stuck to something. I used to have crazy, repetitive dreams that often left me exhausted in the morning. I listen to a deep sleep session every night and since day one my mind feels clear and rested in the morning.

Wow, this app is amazing! I have really bad anxiety and usually can't sleep. At first, when my therapist recommended this to me, i thought it wouldnt work but now, almost 6 months later, i get enough sleep almost every night! Thank you, Calm. Its really helped me

This app is amazing. Prices are a little high, but I think it's worth it. After doing any of the meditations, I feel completely relaxed, and most of the times I fall asleep. I recommend for anyone with anxiety, or anyone with a busy life and they are trying to relax once in a while.

A life saver, almost literally. Been meditating for a few months now after suffering from severe depression and hitting an all time low this year. Meditation has helped me change my life and I've had a significant turnaround. 100% worth the ¬£36 for a years membership. Mindfulness is a very important tool in keeping yourself healthy. Thank you Calm, and major thanks to Tamara too! üñ§

I treated myself to the premium version of this app at the end of last year and I am so glad I did I used to meditate regularly when I was suffering with anxiety but never managed to get back into the habit unless I'm feeling ill. This app makes it so easy for me to meditate daily, I love there is one ready for me every day if I wish to use it or I can search for others if I am looking for something specific, which I did a couple of weeks ago when I was anxious about public speaking

This is something that everyone needs in their lives. I started this at least 3 months ago. My habit is now to listen every day and/or night and it really really helps with centering myself to live fully. So happy I found this and I would never pay for an app like this in the past, but it is worth it.

I usually have a hard time to sleep, not only that but feel good when I sleep.. calm changed that for me ever since I've been using it, it's helped with my sleeping and every time I wake up i feel like I've had a long 8 hr sleep even if it's really 6 hrs I just feel so good when i wake up.

So far, I really enjoy the guided beginner meditation practices. I have meditated for a few years, but wanted to experience their take on certain concepts and it seems great so far. I did have one issue after subscribing where it didn't recognize my sub, and kept telling me to buy again, but a reinstall fixed it easily.

Pretty happy with it. The Sleep Stories occupy my mind with something calming, which helps me fall asleep. The GDPR story is particularly helpful. Sleep Story search and ratings could be improved by weighting or filtering in or out categories or tags. E.g. I like some narrators more, have tastes in topics, and want to filter out 'magical Christmas stories' (whether popular or not). I'd like to queue up stories that seem promising without saying I like them yet.

Like an old friend..... Evey day I look forward to visiting with Calm. Beautiful voices, diverse topics, always something new but you can depend on the same old (in a good way) familiar voices and meditations. It really is like a relationship, you visit daily, get filled up with positivity and encouraging words. Well done Calm!

The daily meditations are a great way to start your day. I like the many options of sleep music too. I'm hoping Calm executives will approach Jared Padalecki to do a meditation series or sleep story, to reach the thousands of troubled teenagers. I know my daughter would listen to him. She sure won't listen to Mom!

For a while I have been trying to get into meditation w/o any success. I've tried other systems just to stop midstream. Using Calm has allow me to relax, stay focus & in the present. The voice is very calming & the techiques are easy. Now when I find myself drifting off, I return to me taking a moment, take a breathe, and return to the present. I would recommed Calm to anyone who has problems with overwhelming thoughts & trying to stay present with the sense of self.

I use the Calm app every single night. I can no longer fall asleep without it! Not only do I love the different sounds I could listen to to help me fall asleep such as the rain or the fan or the outdoors but I also love the stories the Sleep stories. This is by far d best thing I have done for myself. I love it

There are so many different topics to explore.The app gives you a lot of tools & it's about the time you take to explore them all & make the most of it.If you really want to.I started with this app a whole ago & used it sporadically because I was too busy or not in the right frame of mind & couldn't sleep so was tired. Recently I reminded myself why I got it & now making an effort to explore it & really open myself up to the wisdom & experience of those who have put it together.so far so great:)

Can't sleep without it I have been meditating for about 17 years but I still get so much out of this app. I have been dx with a chronic illness, pain,nero issues and more ,the app helps remind me to stay on track to reduce the anxiety that can come with high pain levels. It helps me slow my brain and body down at bedtime creating a healthier sleep routine and more restorative sleep which I have struggled with for years.The stories are also great to help distract from pain using visualization

My seven year old son and I love to use Calm on a daily basis. I find it wonderful for helping him relax if he's had a busy or hard day at school, or even if he's a little hyper. Personally I use it to also relax, take stock and just breathe. It's really helped me with my sleep issues and find the sounds and stories irreplaceable at this stage. I particularly love any stories that bring me on a journey to other lands, via train especially. Thank you all at Calm for bringing calm to our lives.

I love this app! I use the night stories to help my 6 year old niece fall asleep. The 10 minute meditations are great. I love the sounds. It is a bit expensive so I'm not sure I can subscribe again, but overall I have enjoyed it!

So I've been reading the negative comments and something stands out: "why pay for something that you can get for free on YouTube?" Well, if you're getting something this good for free, then it means that someone is not getting paid for their work. Excellent app, I've been using it daily for 2 years now. I paid the yearly subscription and it is wayyy worth the price !

Very helpful for sleep. Looking forward to more sleep stories Calm team! The only thing is that sometimes the App forgets that I am a premium customer and I have to close it and reopen it to access the stories. But it's great.

The moshi stories are my babysitter secret. I watch a lot of kids of all ages and always stuggle with getting them to sleep on time (which is natural - it's hard for kids to fall asleep when they know mom and dad are not home) I have started playing the stories for kids and it never fails that they are asleep before the story is over!

This is my ME time in my hectic schedule. I look forward to my Daily Calm in the morning and then later, I can use the other guided meditations to work on specific areas of life. The Master classes are great for listening to in my car. I've even used the bedtime stories a couple of times. They are very descriptive and help you to drift off, leaving the day behind you. I feel like I got my money's worth within the first week!

It's a Game Changer! I suffer from chronic insomnia and anxiety. I don't like taking medication so I thought I'd give this a try. The sleep meditations have helped me sleep deeply and wake up feeling rested. The meditation exercises help me learn mindfulness. This has been a valuable skill for Wellness.
