Calm is the best guided meditation app I've tried so far. I subscribed to headspace before I found Calm and I paid three times Calm's price for an annual subscription which I did not know is unrefundable. Anyway, I did not like it but I found Calm affordable and way better. I definitely recommend Calm to anyone who wants to improve their mind and body health. Thanks Calm team. keep up the great work.

worth every penny. always works well. and the content is amazing. I started using the sleep stories, but now I use the daily calm, mindful eating, and naps as well. I've used it for over a year and haven't gotten bored with the content either. they always add new stuff.

I am naturally sceptical and have found meditation difficult when attempting in the past. Like anything, it comes with practice, we can not expect results with the flick of a switch. This app and the meditations for anxiety and sleep really do help!! I need to spend more time on it and practice the meditations but this app it having a tangible positive effect :-)

Calm is a great app for beginner and experienced meditators alike - I've personally used it for around 3 years now. It has played an important role in seeing me through some periods of tumultuous mental health, as well as everyday good times. Here's some loving kindness for the Calm team and its affiliates. Keep up the great work and thank you for your continued positive influence on my life.

I originally got the free version and decided I liked it so much that I would splurge and subscribe. This app is worth every penny. I can get to sleep quicker and sleep more soundly. Anytime I hear anyone talking about sleep woes I recommend this app.

It's a really great app. I've tried multiple meditation/sleep apps and for me this one works the best. My only change would be to have a way to loop sleep stories/music. Often when I fall asleep, I wake up when the story ends and I have to grab my phone and restart it.

Love this app! The sleep stories, music, and guided meditations are all so wonderful. It's easy to start meditating if you're a first timer. The stories help me get to sleep fast and it's totally worth the yearly cost because it's significantly improving my life. Seriously. üòÉ

I've struggled with sleep for years, with this I can regulate my breathing and listen to a plamned meditation until I doze off. I don't particularly like the female narrator, however you can change this in the settings of the meditation. Many courses on a range of things, I'm currently at Stress and Focus. Calm is usuable without premium and that's how I've experienced it mostly. Helped with my heart rate, anxiety levels and sleep; I've recommend to friends and I recommend here.

I am enjoying this app! It's nice to hear a bedtime story even when you are all grown up! I have stayed at a renowned Spa where I attended a guided meditation session and Calm's guided meditation speakers are just as good if not better than those I listened to at the spa.

I love this app! It makes meditation easy to learn and keep with it. It has a variety of programs so everyone can find something to relate to. And sleep meditations too with awesome sleep stories! I usually fall sleep before they end!

Have found it has helped me improve several aspects of my life. A great support, upfront with cost and bought a one year subscription for a close friend who loved it too. I've cancelled it before with no problem and rejoined. Simple and effective.

I started using the Calm app during a period of extreme anxiety last year. It helped me regulate and get control again. I use it almost every day. There is much to explore and there seems to be something for most situations. I would love to see a search feature in addition to the broad genres. Please keep these great work.

We got this to help our son fall asleep, bit soon found we were using it more than he was! A wonderful way to take both quick and longer breaks to reatore your sanity in a crazy, busy world. From 90 second exercises to hour long body scans, from classic sotries to calming music, this app is well worh the investment

I'm not your "typical" type of person who meditates or any engages in other sort of mindfulness, so when I first got referred to Calm I went about my business and never gave it a second thought. After a few more times having this app recommended, I decided to give it a shot. I'm now on day 4 of using this app and would easily recommend it to anyone seeking to gain focus, become mindful or just shed stress of every day life.

I can't imagine starting my day without the 10 minute daily meditation. I also listen to the masterclass speakers and use calm kids with my children. I have shared it with many friends because of the difference it has made in the way I handle stress and depression.

I've had calm for a few years now and have a subscription. I go through phases when I used the app everyday and others when I don't. I think it's a really good app to help you relax. I would 100% reccomend this as it helps me with sleep and anxiety problems. There's so much to offer all in one place.

cant live without my Calm app!! For 2 years now Calm. has been helping me sleep. It's the best app in the world with the most sleep stories. Not just for Adults but for children too. my daughter loves to listen to the stories. It's well worth the price.

Absolutely love the sleep stories and the deep sleep meditation. For someone who suffers from chronic insomnia and wasn't a believer of meditation, this app had really turned it around ! I would love it though if there was a casting option to chrome cast on my google home to have better sound quality

This app has really helped in learning mindfulness and the talk through meditation really helped staying focused on how to do the meditation. I have used this app for quite some time now and tried out different meditation programs but keep coming back to this app. Thank you for this huge database of so many different techniques to meditation and mindfulness.

I love the options for meditation and the sleep stories. I wish there were more sleep stories or longer ones at times. The music section is also great. Overall this app is worth every penny. I am so grateful for the app.

Calm has been my saving grace. My first introduction to meditation was through this app and it has changed my life. I have had a lifetime of trauma and almost couldn't pull out of it, but Calm has offered me a way to dive inward and find some peace. It is an amazing app for beginners to meditation...but also for people who have been meditating for awhile. I have been using this app for over 2 years and tried many different meditations...Calm is the only one that actually calms me... everytime.

Awesome app! worth every penny too! It has an amazing collection of meditations, sleep stories and beneficial stories, it has support for stress, eating problems, anxiety, personal growth and all sorts! I use this most days and I highly recommend to everyone!

I absolutely love Calm. Ive tried other aps to help me be more constant with meditation and i feel lile calm has helped me to that best. I do enjoy the series, which I often come to, but I think having the Daily Calm is really what does it for me. Often I find myself amazed by how "on-point" they are in my life and how I needed exactly that. furthermore, the soundscapes really play a positive role in my experience.

A lovely lovely app .. I've only just started today as a trial but it's helped me so much with my anxiety and thoughts. I'm learning how to meditate by Jeff warren I can honestly say those 10 minutes were the best I've felt in a very long time. Can't wait for Day 2! I'm forever indebted to all lovely people behind Calm.

I absolutely love this app! From the meditation to the sleep soundscapes which you can set a timer to! I love love love that! Thank you very much to the content creators and the designers also whoever else worked on this. You all are the best!

I can't rate the app itself since I didn't use it, but their customer service gets 5 stars. I downloaded this by mistake and when it charged me $60 I got a refund back in a day. I tried to change my original review and couldn't for some reason so he is my second, I guess.

I love this app. I have a terrible problem with insomnia and anxiety and this app is so worth having for me. It turns my mind off with soothing stories they read, music, meditation and sound of nature. This app everyone should have. Aspecially now when our world is so full of illness and death of so many.

I've used a this and Headspace both for a little while now and so far I prefer Calm. The voice is just more soothing in the basic meditation lessons and I'm intrigued by lots of the other series that are available, especially the Stoicism one with Ryan Holiday. So five stars for Calm, and probably 4.5 for Headspace. I'll likely switch back and forth between them.

Great app, well worth the money. Really helped with my anxiety. Feel happier and more relaxed. Enjoyable to use. Lovely relaxing meditations and great stories. Loads of content and plenty to navigate around never gets boring. Would 100% recommend. Love it.

**Edited 7 Sep 19 to add - subsequent update seems to have been effective and full functionality restored. Back to daily meditations from the "7 days of" series and now also enjoying the Calm Body videos. Aug 19- Loved this app and recommended loads bit since last update have not been able to open ANY of the meditations without the app crashing. Can do the sleep bits and the daily calm, but not e.g. the Calming Anxiety etc. They were my favourite part so app is useless without these.
replyContent: Hi there, I'm so sorry to hear your app is crashing! Reach out to support@calm.com and we'd be happy to help you troubleshoot.

content: Great app. Easy to navigate, simple and beautiful interface, makes it easy to practice meditation especially for beginners like myself. The daily calm is a good feature and I like the selection of different sounds to Listen to.

I love how this app brings a whole new aspect of mental health into my life. The emergency meditations help me if I feel anxious or can't focus, and the sleep stories put me out in 5 minuets max. The music is also amazing for my massage practice. I couldn't recommend this app more, and I'm eager to see what their new content is.

An awesome site. I have found peace and serenity and calmness I never new. I have even introduced my mom to this method of relaxation and she has found sleep. I have learned to take a deep breathe first before I react to my child. Best site ever!!

Wish I'd found it sooner - I've used it every day of the 146 days I've had it, and I certainly feel the benefit. Some great advice in the daily meditations and the sleep stories are terrific for sending me off (and back) to sleep.

Great app with so much content to offer. Even with the free version you get a good bit to get you started. The scenes are very relaxing and probably my favorite part! Really helps to calm anxiousness and to breathe.

I'm the last person that I thought would ever practice meditation. I'm ADHD and I've never been able to do it.. until I started using Calm. These aren't just "guided meditations".. they're classes that teach you how, why, and what to do when you're struggling, and many other things. It's only been 30 days and I'm already able to focus and hold space for people in a way that I've never been able to in my life. Tamara Levitt and Jeff Warren are gods. Use this app everyday.. you'll thank me later.

I basically never write reviews, but this app os awesome - so awesome, that I actually paid for the subscription (which is something else I hardly ever do). While for me meditating has never come easy, this app with its guided meditation helps immensely; "releasing anxiety" has been one of thr mist beneficial series so far, and the sleep stories do just that - help me fall asleep. Thanks to the Calm team! My wish though: choice of male and female voice for ALL meditations and stories!

I love falling asleep to these stories. My sleep is so much deeper after listening to one as well. I love the meditation at my fingertips anytime. When we travel and my kids have trouble falling asleep in different beds, the kids sleep stories are like magic that put them right to sleep.

After creating your account you'll see a blue page with purple bottom says 'Unlock Calm'. On this page on bottom, it says 'Try 7 Days Free' inside an oval that says 'CONTINUE'. Underneath that, it says '$59.99 per year after FREE 7-day trial'. IF YOU DON'T WISH TO PAY FOR A SUBSCRIPTION, click on the 'X' on the top-left hand corner. DO NOT CLICK ON 'CONTINUE'. I have not paid for subscription but even with it's limited selection for non-subscribers it's still great! Hope this helped.

I am a therapist, working with different clients this app help me to successfully include meditation and mindfulness in my sessions. I personally love sleep music at night. My spouse have told me the music has helped her sleep quality since we started listening to it, now it's our daily routine!

I have the free version and there are great meditations on here for those who have some understanding of meditation or who have meditated before. Plus there is lovely music that you can access for free that is relaxing and some are short but others are an hour long to assist you get through tasks either at work or home. Overall a very helpful app. I got the full version and WOW! so glad I did. 6 stars if I could ü§©. Their Series on different types of concerns are very helpful. Highly recommend

I've never been able to mediate for long or sustain a practice before this app came along. (I've tried a couple of the others, but they didn'rt resonate with me.) The sleep stories are a great touch, and I look forward to taking the master classes, too. Really nicely done.

I love this app because in a very busy life and world it helps remind you to take a few moments for reflection, meditation and prayer. The positive quotes it gives you at the end of the session are something you can share with everyone to uplift their spirit. Highly recommend it to anyone!

I love calm so much. I listen to the sleep stories when I go to sleep. I am usually out within the first 20 minutes if it's an hour long. if the app didnt cost so much it would be even better! overall it's pretty amazing! I love yoga and the benefits it adds to my life. calm made it that much easier to get in tune with life in general ‚ô°

I enjoy this app very much. Only 2 lessons and I feel like a more calm and swlf centered person. I highly recommend this to really anyone as everyone can improve on well being and a good state of mind. The only downside to this app is the cost but that is to be expected for someone of this high quality.

This app is AWESOME! It taught me how to successfuly meditate. I've tried for years to learn how to meditate to be able to have better control of my emotions and behavior. The Masterclasses are very informative. Its way more than a meditation app it has sleep stories, music, breathing and more!

This is unlike any App. It helps every area of mental and physical health with unlimited information to be healthy and happy. I believe that is FAR more important than going to the Dr. and getting on meds. NO negative side effects of the info you learn, unlike all the side effects and dependence on medication. This can be life changing if you put as much effort in to it as you do searching for the "right" Dr., or medication. This is best described as accountability on living healthy and HAPPY!

I do love calm but wish i had even more nature stories. I love the descriptive words which make me fall asleep but without being bored. I'd like a new story much more often since i listed every night and have already listed to all the videos. Great app with lots of features other than just stories.

This is such a good app. It helps me fall asleep fast , as a kid who has to wake up at 5 am every week day I need my sleep it this real helps me do that. I recommend this if you have problem sleeping, there is multiple noises your can listen but also some story thing to help you relax and release stress.
it is a good sleep app

I love the Calm app, it is so relaxing and yet eye-opening at the same time. I never realized how much I needed and would love meditating! I've tried a couple other meditation apps, but this one has been by far the best. It is easy to navigate, has great speakers, and so many other benefits!

I love Calm. Over time I have made it s daily practice. The is something for any moment of your day (calm days and stress packed days) from a spare 1 minute in the day to a peaceful open ended self meditation. I've tried other popular apps but have come back to calm due to the variety and constant new features - love it!

I love it so much I use it every night I especially love the story's where the mostly evil characters learn kindness I think it's a awesome app if i could I would listen to the story's all day long my favorite story is probably... I don't even now all the story's are amazing!!! Keep up the good work I will definitely tell all my friend's

I love this app. As someone who has suffered with anxiety for a large chunk of her life, this app is a god send. I listen to the sleep stories every night, which are just so calming. Only thing I would add is more Jerome Flynn stories, particularly fiction ones! His voice is so relaxing.

Have just started meditating and this app has been so helpful. I try to use it every morning and I LOVE the morning stretch. I have also listened to the sleep stories, although they work so well I have yet to finish one. My day starts much smoother and calm when I make time for these simple things.

I love the app. It's a shame you have to pay to get everything though. It does have beneficial programs that runs through it. Such as sleep meditation and Reducing anxiety. Or Books that will be read to you. Songs, etc.

Best white noise for my baby! I connect this to a bluetooth speaker and use the feature that let's me play noise for 12 hours straight. It plays white noise which he needs to sleep all night long. Saves us money on any pricey subscriptions and pricey noise machines! I love this app. Been using it for meditation since before my son was born :)

Love this app, I always struggle to turn my mind off and get to sleep, would often be lying in bed for at least an hour trying to switch off and fall asleep. With this app I'm able to fall asleep within half an hour! Definitely recommend

I received a paid subscription as a gift from my cousin/sister/friend. We have weekly conversations that run the gamut of life's experiences. Recently, I have struggled more than usual emotionally, physically and spiritually. All forms of readings for inner peace, medications for anxiety and moderate alcohol was of little or no avail. Calm is my answer to more manageable anxiety/stress and restful sleep. Thus far I am on my ninetieth (90) day streak. I could continue go on, but it's Calm time.

Excellent app! I have been sleeping much better thanks to the night meditation, and I am really setting my day up for success by also doing the morning meditation. I love the variety and the different sessions available, I can always find the right meditation, even if I only have 5 minutes!! thank you!!

So very helpful! From beginning my day, to stressful situations at work, to helping fall asleep and get back to sleep when I wake up, this app does it all. I also have a chronic pain condition. Calm helps me deal with the pain and the medical procedures I need.

This app is very user friendly and has numerous listening options. It is also visually beautiful. i would love if there were some "calm talks" to listen to while engaged in different activities, such as driving.

The music will play when your phone/device is off, and play behind most apps automatically. (Not apps like tiktok or youtube) it really does help me study, work, sleep, etc. Theres music for all kinds of tastes, and it's free, with so many songs!

I have used CALM for several years. The sleep stories in particular have helped me fall asleep countless times. I use them mostly when I wake up in the middle of the night and can't get back to sleep. They're amazing. Often I don't think anything will help, but I play a story and the next thing I know, my alarm is going off. I've given subscriptions to both my daughters in college. Thank you.

I've been using this app for a year now. I recently tried using another popular one but I find this price point and the value from Calm to be better. The amount of content for meditation and sleep stories keeps me on this one. Has helped me keep my meditation routine going which is having benefits I see every day.

Meditations are sophisticated while succinct. Exquisite, literary, deeply insightful - readings have a lovely pace in just the right portions to help me slow down & absorb the moment. I love the sleep stories & readings the most. Always learning from this app. As a writer, musician & preacher I appreciate the nuanced writing & subtle, skilled vocalists.

Calm is a wonderful multipurpose app. I was a beginner meditator and I enjoy the guided meditations as they have deepened my practice. I also find the five minutes stretches helpful during long days of sitting as they walk me through the moves. Finally the sleep stories are a great way to fall asleep faster and mire deeply than watching tv or even reading because you can turn off all your lights and close your eyes.

The best app I've found by a long way. It does everything I want and some. Can't fault it. My only gripe is the ¬£37 subscription fee so I'm only using free stuff, but even that is quite something. The overall quality is amazingly good. If you're looking for an app to help you relax, look no further.

On the recommendation of a mental health course I took, I started using Calm to learn mindfulness. Since starting to use it three months ago, I have overcome my depression completely and am starting to work on my anxiety. I particularly liked the Untangling Physical Pain and 7 Days of Soothing Pain practises. They have helped me not only accept my chronic illness but also helped me learn acceptance as a whole. This app has honestly been a lifesaver for me and I am so thankful.

Really great app; for me personally an enabler to mediate more fequently due to also offering good daily short meditiations (10 min)! And of course next to that longer sessions and sets to work on specific items such as stress, anxiety, sleeping, stretching,... thank you for this app!

The Calm app has helped me through some of my most difficult challenges and continues to help me understand myself and others. I am still learning how to live with my emotions and most of all live in the moment. I had never meditated before but, my doctor recommended the Calm app and I am so thankful he did!

Calm provide really great meditation/mindfullness tracks which allow me to start stilling my mind and overcoming anxiety. Tamara's voice and speed of talking are just right. The sleep stories I have listened to thus far are really good and most enjoyable. Content and voices so far have been great and helped me still my mind. The daily calm is something I look forward to, to start my day. Five months of using Calm has really helped and I am not stopping, it is part of my life now.

i never could've imagined sleeping past 2 hours at a time, that is until Calm! Using the guided meditation and listening to soothing voices read stories I never hear endings to have improved my life by increased sleep and less stress daily. I cannot stop talking about this app to those i know!!

Calm is awesome! There are so many different sessions tailored to the areas of life that matter to you most. I'm really liking the Calm Body section right now. The app is easy to use and fun to explore and find new sessions I hadn't noticed before.

I love Tamara Levitt's voice, her guidance, and the variety of meditations and calming sounds. I have been a subscriber for two years now. I am doing the meditations pretty consistently and am noticing a difference in my demeanor overall and that is with just 10 minutes a day. Highly recommend!

I have a lot of monkey mind, in this app allows me to center myself very quickly. I've even brought it into small meetings at work when everybody's stressed out and they are very thankful to experience the calming effects that can be attained within 10 minutes.
so calming and peaceful

I've only just started using it, but love the calm voices, background sounds and guidance. I feel more balanced afterwards. With regular use, I can only see myself being more present and having more to offer this life.

The introductory course and the subsequent 21 day course has been incredible for teaching mindfulness and the importance of it in everyday life. In addition, the sleep stories are amazing for falling asleep! I wish some stories could be narrated by both male and female voices though.

This app is amazing! I have a very short fuse and little to no patience and Calm breathe sessions and music (what I most often use) helps to calm me. I do not pay for the premium version bc there is plenty to offer without doing so! Check it out for relax time

I only use the free meditations. The host's voice is so soothing and I love that I have options for how long and how directed I want to be. I have A.D.D. so using the shorter and guided meditations has helped me find confidence in being able to sit still and at peace and helped me work up to slightly longer and less guided meditations. I love that I can use the app to take a 5 minute break during my day. Highly recommend, even if you only use the free version.

Love this app! Whether you take 10 minutes to meditate or just use the "breathe" feature for a minute to calm yourself and recenter in the middle of your day, it's an outstanding reminder to always return to the breath.

I Love Calm. For those nights when sleep alludes you, Calm gently brings it to your weary body and brain. Rarely is the night that I complete a Bedtime Story, for I have drifted off to sleep. The narrator's voices are relaxing, especially as they slow and drift away as the story ends. Thank you so much for this wonderful, sleep welcoming app.

Dear Calm App, I honestly haven't utilized this app to its full potential. However I didnt realize that my free trial ended and was wondering if there was any way you could issue a refund? I tried submitting a request through the app but the captcha kept failing/wouldnt load. There is definitely no way I can pay off the 59.99 and the 35 overdraft fee from my bank. I hope to hear back from someone soon, Thank you, -Colleen M

This is the bast app for calm. Its benefits me a lot it is organised very beautifully and very easy to use also. And it has a lot of ways of calm, Mediation and so on. That's not all you will get to see so many different and interesting life image with natural noise that you gonna love for sure. . Believe me you gonna love to follow the audio instruction it is effective. I really enjoy a lot and you can use it to bring calm in life.

I was a real cynic about meditation but forced myself into it with the help of Calm following recommendations from others. It has massively improved my outlook on life and how I cope with day to day stressors. I highly recommend this to anyone looking to increase their positivity and/or feel more content with what they have. Stick with it when you first start - it took me a while to get into it properly but it's well worth the perseverance!

I wasn't sure what I would get with this app. It turns out I love it. I started with just utilizing the stories, music and meditations that where free but I have decided to unlock it all. It is amazing. I love putting on Thunderstorms and reading a book to unwind from a long day of nothing but stress. I highly reccomend this app to everyone I work with.

Simple, user-friendly Meditation sessions. Great guided sessions for someone just starting out, and unguided options for the more experienced practitioner. Great variety of options and topics, from reducing anxiety, managing stress, dealing with emotions, and improving sleep. There are even options for kids!

I absolutely love it this has helping hands everywhere and on just about anything you can imagine I wish it was just a little less expensive because I am a single dad and I can't afford to pay for the membership fee for the year. But love the app about time someone made something useful and helpful thank you calm

I love this app! The meditations are great, I love the sleep stories and the nature soundscapes too. 10 mins a day makes a huge difference in how I feel. Well worth buying. Try the 7 day trial and go for it. üòÄ

Love this app. Totally worth the subscription. I use it for stretches and meditation, plus the music is great for background as I work. My daughter listens to the sleep stories... They put her out like a light!

I appreciate the variety of helps in different areas you can focus on such as stress or sleep. I also appreciate the variety of backgrounds, music, and sounds that are well developed to aid in focusing on specific aspects of the experience of meditation.

Calm has a great interface and really does help the mind slow down. I love that their customer service is just as amazing. I had a query about my subscription and they immediately replied and fixed everything. Thank you!

I have never tried meditation before. I was surprised that this was so effective for me - super relaxing! Was like doing cache cleaning on my brain, haha. Would definitely recommend that everyone try this just once and see if it's effective. The narrators' voices are super soothing. I love the thunderstorm sounds! :-D

A coworker recommended this to me, because I was suffering from a 5-day stretch of insomnia. Learning how to tune in to yourself is a journey I'm willing to embark upon. Now, I'm meditating every morning and evening. I'd recommend this app to anyone looking to get into mindfulness, meditation, or is having trouble sleeping.

I try to implement some of the ideas from "The Daily Calm".It has yielded positive results.Still to practice a lot of good ideas.The message at the end of the talks are superb.I share it with my near and dear ones.I also find interesting talks under "Meditate".For example "Breaking habits" ,"Focus".I also I love the soothing music. Mindfulness is a very practical tool for learning awareness moment to moment and is dealt very effectively in the Daily Calm through the soothing voice of Tamara.

I've tried meditation apps before to help with anxiety, but have always felt like daily meditation was a chore more than a choice... until I downloaded Calm. Calm has totally changed my life! Through this app not only have I learnt how to meditate, but now I actually look forward to escaping life for just ten minutes. I was sceptical, but Calm has really helped me to take control of my mental health. I have paid for the full app, and never regretted it, a tiny price to pay for a happy mind.

I really like this app. I love using the sleep stories to fall asleep and in the middle of the night when I wake up instead of turning on tv. Also, guided meditations are easy for those of us who are new to meditating. I highly recommend this app.

I'm usind the free version but contemplating unlocking the premium. The video and audio is a very cool touch. The app is simple to use and navigate. I think it has an elegant and contemporary look. The speakers are clear and easy to listen to. Keep it up, Calm team!

This app is amazing I can live again! I've been having sleep prosalise and now it's not as horrible and creepy as it was. My Anxity has lowered down and that's amazing! I'm so Calm and happy well "happier",really this is amazing thank you to the creaters for this app my whole world has just releasted this oxygin and this weight has been lifted off my sholders i'm the happiest i've been in years. Thank you.

Meditation has been such an important addition to my mental, emotional, and physical well-being. However, I did not know where to begin or how to continue the practice. "Calm" has been perfect for me given the coaching and guidance it provides and sessions tailored to what I need or what I'm feeling. For anyone looking to live a healthier life, I can't recommend this app enough.

I really love this app and have purchased the lifetime membership. The app has multiple backgrounds with various ambient soundtracks for meditation and I like that I can personalize my experience. The app has a large number and variety of meditations, and offers choice over narrator. I have greatly enjoyed the daily meditation and have done a number of the other meditations on offer. Using the app regularly has been beneficial and it is noticable when I don't. Highly recommend it.

We have used this app for well over a year. Everyone in my family loves the Sleep stories. I use the app for meditating and for anxiety. There is alot of context in each section and I haven't yet listened to everything yet! It has especially been helpful for the kids, when they are anxious.

Good app I am from brazil and I worried a bit it would be a bit hard to use it since portuguese is my native language but english used was easy and the instructions to relax were plain and i immediately tune. it relaxed me a lot to listen to the woman and the water stream on the background while she direted me to relax. i recommend it.

I've had this app for 2 yrs and counting!! Lots of tools and aids to assist in mindfulness & growing from the inside out. I love their daily calms, but there are also so many other wonderful meditations to chose from depending on your current mood or situation. The breathe section is perfect for places you cannot listen to a meditation and are able to still recenter and calm yourself silently. I also love their master classes filled with great resources and information on different topics.

Something feels different... All I did was the introductory to meditation by Jeff Warren but listening to the calming background noises while following the directions given, I feel different. More relaxed already. I'm honestly excited to see how far this feeling can go. I'll try to update later.

its great...very relaxing...i wish the sleep stories were longer tho...it would be nice if you could make a "PLAYLIST" so you keep getting stories while you sleep...for some reason i always wake up within minutes of my sleep story ending...PLAYLIST-PLAYLIST-PLAYLIST!!! overall worth the money...üòéüò¥üò¥

Really helps my sleep. Before this app i would play netflix or movies in the background to sleep. Yet that was counterproductive as it was stimulating my brain instead of relaxing it. Calm is perfectly made to listen to before bed and put you in the right mindset to have a full sleep.

Fantastic app. Really great for before sleep, morning meditations or mindfull pauses during the day. Has been a wonderful tool for my mental health. Also love the music to just chill out for a while. No tech issues, have been using for maybe 3 years

replyContent: Hi there, I'm so sorry for the trouble! We've released a hotfix (4.11.3) to resolve the audio stopping issue. Reach out to support@calm.com and we'd be happy to answer any questions!

content: I love Calm. I am a teacher and mom to a 4 and 6 year old. When I hit the pillow I always have a hard time sleeping. Since using Calm I fall asleep with 10-15 minutes and get amazing sleep. My kids love the kid stories, and my students enjoy the melodies as well while they work.

After mastering my physical and nutritial health, my mind was the clear next area of focus for me. I discovered this calm app rhru Samsung Health one night and decided to try it out. Calm has an interesting format. First the soothing voice of Tamara leads the breath work followed by a period of silence. Then the lesson for today and the dismissal. There are also sections to remind you about keeping up attendance. All in all a very satisfying app with plenty of scope for growth.

Wonderful app. very user friendly - you get what you pay for. If its too expensive for you... use the free version. ridiculous number of 1 star reviews on here because of internet entitlement. Stephen Fry, Matthew McConaughey and Moby ain't developing content for free.

calm and peaceful.

This is the best mindfulness and meditation app I've ever used. I love it! I don't see myself ever deleting it or not paying the membership rate. It is worth it and makes you feel so alive. I believe every single person should meditate and Calm would be beneficial in each and every one of our lives.

There is a session for every mooth. Chose your favorite voice for your guidance. I love the app. Much possibilities if it is to bring more focus in your life, feel less anxiety or to get to sleep again. Calm can assist you in the way that you prefer.

Great app for learning to relax (yes it's hard for some of us). I have severe Adhd and ocd, so it's difficult for me to stop and focus on one thing, this app has helped me to focus and relax.

My favourite app. I do my meditation on the commute to work and it is always a great way to start the day. The subscription is well worth the money. The sleep stories help when I'm restless and can't get to sleep.

I tried many other guided meditation apps and ended up subscribing to Calm because of the sessions available, Tamara's voice and teaching and the Masterclasses. I've had it for many months now, close to a year, and I use it (almost) daily.

The Calm app has been an informative and practical tool for my mindfulness practice. I love Tamara's gentleness! It is helpful that there is a meaningful flow in practice sets as well as a variety of options to customize your own experience if desired. You can use the app lightly or very routinely and benefit from either. My children like to use Calm with me sometimes as well.

The first time I tried this it worked perfect to make me sleep my all time favorite is the blue gold story. It made me fall asleep really quick.you should get this app if you want to help with anxiety, sleep problems, or to help you keep calm. I have anger issues and when u get mad I put blue gold and I get calm fast and u have really bad anger issues. I get mad super fast but with this app I also get clam super fast too.
I love the selections for the sleep stories! I sleep withing minutes, I always have trouble sleeping so this helped me a lot. The meditation has also helped as this is my first time ever doing it.

Over the past year I've been dealing with a great deal of anxiety and panic attacks, as well as palpitations. I took courses in meditation and mindfulness and discovered Calm, and also have been seeing a doctor. The courses have helped immensely and the ongoing daily use of Calm is a treasure. Calm has helped so much with stress, attitude, and being overwhelmed. I'm filled with gratitude! Also, I want to express rave reviews for the incredible creativity of Tamara, and beautiful spirit.

its absolutely amazing. I've learnt so much from the Calm Masterclass. The meditation each day is refreshing with a wonderful little lesson. I love the sleep stories, music, sounds etc. The nature sounds, allow me to feel as if I am really in nature and relax me. Just what I need for stress.

I love this app so much. It has so many meditations on a variety of aspects of mindfulness to give you an excellent tool box whatever your mood or emotional state you can find something that will help you be more aware and grounded.

Depression is something I have been battling for the longest time. I am an introvert; hence I find it so hard to open up to people. I tried therapy, but it was too much for me. One of my friends suggested this app, and after I downloaded it, the first message I came across made my heart smile, and I knew everything is going to be okay. The app has been of great help with the fantastic content it offers, such as perfect music and bedtime stories. It has excellent designs and is easy to use. It provides peace and serenity in so many ways. I had a tough time falling asleep, but after I started using this app, the music and the bedtime stories make me sleep like a baby. It has helped me with anxiety, and the action plan that comes with the app enables me to prepare for the future. The app is costly, but it is worth the money.

*Based solely on a technical aspect and not the quality of the app content- I turned this on last night before bed and when I woke up, the app screen was still up and running which means the one image of the Calm screen was on all night. Not good for phones. Please update this so screens will be allowed to go into sleep mode and not run continuously.

content: I really love this app, lots of choice, content updates regularly, I've been using for 6 months and I still have so much to explore as well as having firm favourites... worth every penny

Used calm since the day i downloaded it. I couldn't get to sleep but this app is unbelievable. I've never had a story where it's ended and I'm awake. Definitely way more resources on here than I am remotely taking advantage of, and while I havent figured out how to implement this with my middle schoolers yet (self-care has been the priority), I am grateful for Calm.

This is amazing. I use it every day. It sets me up in the morning. I love the short little exercises. I use them when things get a little fraught. Very happy with this app. I use it with bluetooth and ear buds.

great app. the nature sounds are amazing. the tools for meditation are helpful. the layout on this is nicer than some of the other apps but I haven't used them all so I have a limited amount to compare this too. but overall 5stars.

Excellent app for daily mindfullness Highly recommend as a daily 10 min help to open a window of calm, and rebalanced for the day.
